title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and serve with raw vegetables.

title: beef tender
directions: Sprinkle lemon pepper on tender, grill on pit for 20 minutes. put in oven with 2 sticks butter, can stay in oven for hours at 200° if needed.

title: brownies
directions: Sift the flour with baking powder and salt.
Melt butter and chocolate over hot water.
Beat eggs well, then add sugar gradually, beating well.
Beat in chocolate mixture.
Mix in flour, then nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Cut crescent rolls into 16 pieces.
Place a piece of apple in each piece of crescent roll.
Place in pan.
Pour melted butter over the crescent rolls.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over melted butter.
Pour orange juice over crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and buttermilk.
Add flour, salt, soda and cereal.
Mix batter thoroughly.
Gently stir in 1 cup blueberries if plain bran is used.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. (Keeps up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.)
Store in container with a tight lid.
When you take out to bake, do not stir.
Just spoon into greased muffin tins or use paper baking cups.

title: sugar 'n spice cupcakes
directions: Make cupcakes as directed on package.
Just before baking, sprinkle batter lightly with confectioners sugar, a little cinnamon (so some white sugar is still visible) and chopped nuts (1 teaspoon for each cupcake).
Bake.

title: pepperoni pizza roll
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in with pastry blender the shortening.
Add milk.
Mix quickly and lightly.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured board.
Knead for 1/2 minute.
Roll out into rectangle, 10 x 12-inch.

title: mediterranean pork
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat; brown pork on both sides.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat, uncovered, 10 minutes or until pork is cooked. Serves 4.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Blend together; spread over layer 2. Spread remainder of Cool Whip on top for final layer.

title: red's perfect casserole
directions: Saute rice and onion in margarine until brown. Add all ingredients in a 3-quart casserole dish. Bake, covered, about 35 minutes at 350°. You can add chicken, pork chops, or any meat you want.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Mix everything, except ginger ale.
Place in freezer overnight.
Stir occasionally to mush.
Just before serving, pour in ginger ale.

title: tomato chop
directions: Mix first four ingredients and let stand overnight.
In morning, drain and add the rest of ingredients.
Don't cook.

title: mexican dip
directions: Put one layer of sour cream, layer of cream cheese, layer of picante sauce, layer of chopped onions, layer of chopped/diced up ham and layer of cheese.
Add black olives, if desired.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Sift flour once, measuring 3 cups.
Sift flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon together.
Beat eggs one at a time in separate bowl; add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add squash and pecans, mixing well.
Bake in 2 well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Delicious served warm with butter.
(Can be wrapped in foil and frozen.)

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil spaghetti and drain well.
Mix Italian dressing and Salad Supreme with noodles.
Add red onion, cucumber and tomatoes and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight or several hours.
This is great for picnics and potlucks.
Enjoy.
Lo-cal, too!

title: beef luau
directions: Combine all ingredients. Shape into 6 patties and brown well on both sides in skillet.
Remove from pan.
Make sauce in pan.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Cool and cube (small).
Place 1/2 of cake cubes in punch bowl.
Add 1/2 of banana slices.
Add 1/2 pudding.
Add 1/2 of pineapple.
Add 1 can strawberry pie filling.
Add 1/2 Cool Whip.
Add 1 cup pecans. Repeat layers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve by scoop or spoonful.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Add can milk, butter, and sugar in to pot and
boil for 5 min. (Turn off heat) Then add,
peanut butter,
jar of marshmallow cream and
vanilla. Mix well, pour out in pan, and
cool in refrigerator. Cut in to small squares and serve.

title: missouri (no bake) cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Cook until mixture comes to full boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oats and mix well. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper until set.

title: ice cream topping
directions: Melt butter or oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add brown sugar and stir.
Add coconut, pecans and Rice Krispies and toast in 300° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Cool and refrigerate.
Can be kept in freezer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut or tear tortillas in 1/4-inch strips.
Mix soups, chilies and onion.
In baking dish, layer tortillas and chicken. Top with soup mixture, layered; also cheese in layer.
Cover top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: crabmeat mold(for dip with crackers)
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Bring soup to a boil.
Take off stove and add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add mayonnaise.
Add cooled soup mixture, celery, onion, drained crab and Worcestershire sauce.
Put in oiled 4-cup mold and refrigerate.
Can make a day ahead (I freeze also). Unmold and serve.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Bring water to a boil; add Jell-O and pineapple.
Mix well. Let cool.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Chill overnight.

title: sour cream coleslaw
directions: Combine all ingredients
in
a large bowl. Chill before serving.

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Arrange slices in a 13x9 inch dish coated with cooking spray. Spread with mustard. Combine breadcrumbs and next 3 ingredients. Sprinkle over tomatoes. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine melted with graham cracker crumbs and press down in dish like crust.
Beat for 15 minutes, 2 sticks margarine, eggs and powdered sugar.
Spread on top of crust.
Slice bananas and lay over mix.
Spread pineapple, over bananas, spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle nuts and cherries on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: shrimp appetizers
directions: Mix shredded cheese, mayonnaise, shrimp, curry, scallions and salt together.
Mound slightly on English muffin half.
Cut each muffin into quarters or smaller.
Place on broiled sheet or rack and broil until bubbly, about 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: elegant spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Cut artichoke hearts in half.
Melt 1 sick butter in a large saucepan.
Add cream cheese, spinach, water chestnuts and garlic salt.
Line a greased baking dish with artichoke hearts and cover with spinach mixture.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: curried chicken and vegetable salad
directions: Whisk in a large bowl until blended the yogurt, mayonnaise, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Add rest of ingredients and toss to mix and coat.

title: hawaii style chicken or pork
directions: Cook over chicken or pork until done in covered dish. Thicken with cornstarch and serve over rice.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except for the coconut.
Cook in the top of a double boiler until thick (at least 20 minutes), then add coconut and let cook a little longer. Pour in two 9-inch prebaked pie shells or graham cracker shells.
Beat egg white and 2/3 cup sugar until stiff and spread on pies.
Sprinkle coconut on top and brown lightly.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottoms only of 2 loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Mix sugar and shortening in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Stir in zucchini, water and eggs.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to mixture; add vanilla. Fold in chopped nuts and raisins.
Pour into pans.
Bake until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 60 or 70 minutes.

title: cucumber mousse
directions: Pour boiling water on gelatin, mixing until dissolved.
Let cool about 10 minutes; add cottage cheese, mayonnaise, onion, cucumber and almonds, if using.
Mix well; pour into mold or glass or ceramic bowl and chill until set.
Yields 6 servings. Preparation Time:
10 minutes.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar and margarine.
Mix well; set aside.
Blend cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, topping mix and cold milk (adding milk slowly) until mixture will be smooth and light after increasing speed to whip on mixer.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Drain cooked potatoes and refrigerate overnight.
Chop the potatoes and mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake in a shallow pan at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: cheese dish
directions: Put mixture in a buttered dish.
Mix well and pour in dish. Bake 1/2 hour in quick oven, 400°.
Serves four.

title: tortellini and spinach casserole
directions: Prepare creamed spinach as label directs.
Prepare tortellini as label directs; drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, mix creamed spinach with milk.
Spoon half of creamed spinach mixture into shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole or 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with half of the tortellini and chopped tomato.
Repeat layering with remaining creamed spinach mixture, tortellini and tomatoes, then sprinkle with basil.
Cover casserole with lid or foil; bake 40 to 45 minutes or until mixture is heated through.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: stupid pie
directions: Mix together and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven in a greased pie tin.
Cool, then top with 1 cup whipping cream.
Use 4x sugar to sweeten cream.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 4 hours.
Can be made the night before.

title: banana chiffon cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Make a well. Add salad oil, egg yolks, water, banana and vanilla and mix well. Beat until smooth.

title: metha's cheese and peas
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Add milk and salt. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Melt in grated cheese and add peas and pimento.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Bring sugar and 1/2 cup water to a boil.
Dissolve cornstarch in 3/4 cup cold water.
Add this to syrup mixture.
Stir constantly while cooking, until thick.
Blend in salt and lemon juice, if desired, and enough red food coloring until bright red. Wash and remove stems from strawberries.
Place in a 9-inch baked pie shell or 1 dozen medium tart shells.
Pour glaze over strawberries and cool.
Top with whipped cream when cool.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt for 5 minutes. Add soda and vanilla.
Pour this over corn and stir.
Bake in oven for 1 hour (250°); stir every 15 minutes.
Put in sealed container and it will keep a long time.

title: easy double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend thoroughly by hand.
Form firm dough.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Flatten ball slightly on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: turkey and biscuit casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat butter in 2-quart casserole in oven until melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients except spinach.
Bake 20 minutes, stirring once, until sauce is slightly thickened. Stir in spinach.
Place 1 can biscuits around edge of casserole. Increase oven temperature to 425°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: sweet-sour cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage and dice onion.
Pour boiling water over cabbage and onion.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Drain.
Add water, tomatoes, butter and apple.
Cook until tender.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt.
Make a roux.

title: ooey gooey chocolate sauce
directions: In a small, heavy saucepan, bring the cream to a bare simmer over low heat.
Place the chocolate pieces in a medium bowl.
Add the cream into the chocolate and let sit for 3 minutes.
Add the vanilla and whisk until the chocolate melts and the sauce thickens.

title: barb's white chocolate candy
directions: Line an 8 x 11-inch pan with foil.
Grease foil with 1 teaspoon butter.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Drain and rinse shrimp.
Refrigerate shrimp in water for 30 minutes.
Cream the cheese and butter together; add lemon to mixture, then chopped onion.
Drain shrimp and add to mixture. Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill for several hours.
Serve with choice of crackers.

title: borsch (vegetable beef soup)(ukranian)
directions: Peel beet and cook it with beef stew meat in a medium size pot. Fill 3/4 of pot with water. Cook on high until it boils. Then reduce to medium to low heat and cook for 1 hour. During this hour peel potatoes and cut into cubes. Shred cabbage.

title: chestnut meatballs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Add the meat and water chestnuts; mix well.
Form into 1/2-inch balls.
Place in a baking pan in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can be frozen after they have cooled and stored for future use.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ketchup.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. When almost done, brush top with ketchup.
Broil until ketchup hardens some.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice pickles and onion and set aside.
Heat together remaining ingredients.
Let cool.
Pour over pickles and onion. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Pack in small jars.
Do not put too much juice in jars.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: layered lasagna
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef in skillet, keeping it crumbly. Spread the bottom of a 2-quart greased baking dish with thin layers of Zippy Sauce, cooking noodles, Parmesan cheese, cottage cheese, cheese slices and meat.
Repeat layers reserving some of the sauce for top with layers of cheese.
Bake in a moderate oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: venison chili
directions: Cook meat in oil.
Add onions and bell peppers.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: cookie crunch
directions: Cream margarine with fork.
Blend in sugar and egg yolk.
Add sifted flour and cinnamon; mix well.
Press onto ungreased 10 x 15-inch baking sheet.
Brush with unbeaten egg white.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: party punch
directions: Mix citric acid and boiling water in a Pyrex container; let stand 24 hours.
Add orange juice, pineapple juice, sugar and water.
The citric acid water will keep in refrigerator several weeks.
Yield:
75 servings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange asparagus spears in bottom of casserole.
Mix soup and juice from water chestnuts.
Add water chestnuts and green peas and mix well.
Pour this mixture over the asparagus in baking dish.

title: pistachio torte
directions: Pat down in a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350 degrees, cool.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit and arrange in casserole.
Melt butter; add other ingredients.
Pour mixture over fruit and bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Store in tightly closed jar. Use 3 to 4 teaspoons to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: *Bread should be toasted for 20 minutes at 250°, then cube. (If using thinly sliced bread, add a couple more slices.)

title: piccalilli(my great-grandmother's recipe, chloe hill)
directions: Mix green tomatoes and onions in nonmetal container; cover with 1 cup salt and let set overnight.
Drain in morning.
Add other ingredients and cook until done.
Put in hot clean jars and seal tightly.
No processing needed.

title: nacho nibbles
directions: Cover a large microwave-safe plate with the nacho chips.
On every chip, put about 1 spoonful of salsa.
Cover the chips with lots of cheese.
Scatter olives on the chips.
Cook in microwave on High or full power for 1 minute and 20 seconds or until the cheese is melted.
Remove from the microwave carefully and serve.

title: crushed vanilla wafer cake
directions: Put crushed wafers, coconut and broken pecan halves in large pan.
Mix this well.
Put butter, sugar, eggs and milk in bowl and mix well.
Pour this mixture into dry mixture and mix well.
Bake at 325° in middle of oven for 1 hour.
Longer it sets, the better it is.

title: bill's sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients; cover and simmer one hour.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Fat free dressings may be used if desired.

title: orange cooler
directions: Place pineapple (including juice) in large pan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
While stirring sprinkle on dry Jello-O.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add nuts and buttermilk.
Stir well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into lightly sprayed 9 X 13-inch pan.
Chill several hours.
Cut into squares. Serve on lettuce leaf.
Garnish with cherry, pineapple chunk, or orange slice.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
In skillet over medium-high heat in hot butter, cook onion and garlic until golden.
Stir in beef and next 5 ingredients.
Cook, stirring until meat is browned.
Stir in soup and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat through.
Do not boil. Serve over noodles.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except coconut in blender.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Soften cheese; mix everything thoroughly.
Make graham cracker crust in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add above mixture.
Top with can of cherry pie filling.

title: mission balls
directions: Boil margarine, milk, dates, vanilla and sugar for 2 minutes on stove.
Add nuts and cereal.
Mix together well.
Form into balls, roll in coconut.
Place on tray lined with wax paper to cool.

title: spring salad
directions: Pinch lettuce and line 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass dish.
Cut onions and tops and layer over lettuce.
Add 1/2 cup chopped celery, then chestnuts.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups frozen uncooked peas.
Mix sugar, mayonnaise and pour over top of all ingredients.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator at least 4 hours.
May be made overnight.

title: cream of tomato basil soup
directions: Heat tomato and leek juices.
Combine potato juice with milk and add to juice mixture.
Cook soup, stirring frequently, until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish with basil leaves.
Serves 4.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Sift flour, salt and soda into mixture.
Mash bananas and add eggs and bananas to mixture until fluffy.
Add nuts (if desired).
Cook in moderate (350°) oven for 40 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in shallow dish (buttered).
Top with Ritz crackers, crumbled, and melted margarine.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: perfect pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add vanilla and salt. Blend in egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour cream. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Use 10-inch tube pan.
Cool in pan for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate crunchola
directions: Mash peanut butter and butter together in mixing bowl with fork.
Stir in granola or oatmeal, chocolate chips, raisins and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
Roll into bite-size balls and coat with shredded coconut.
Store leftover Crunchola in refrigerator.

title: ambrosia 2
directions: Mix all together.
Serve cold. Tastes like you cut up fresh oranges and added to this.

title: better than potato salad
directions: In large bowl, combine rice, radishes, eggs, cucumber, celery, and onion. Make a dressing of mayonnaise, mustard, and salt; mix well and pour over rice mixture; toss. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, peanuts, Karo and salt in microwave-safe glass bowl. Cook 8 minutes on High.
Remove and add butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from microwave and add soda.
Mix well until frothy.
Pour quickly onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower as directed.
Drain.
Put in casserole dish as follows.
Layer of vegetables, pats of butter, chunks of Velveeta cheese.
Alternate until vegetables are used up.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until heated through.
Use plenty of cheese and butter.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
If you like, you may sprinkle more cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 1/2 cups of boiling water.
Stir in strawberries, sugar and salt.
Cool until it begins to thicken. Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix mixture with angel food cake.
Press into a cake pan.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours to set.
Cut into squares. Top with Cool Whip and/or strawberries.

title: chicken con tortilla
directions: Cook and debone chicken breasts.
Cut into pieces.
Mix soups with milk.
Add onions and tortillas.
Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/3 tortilla mixture, 1/2 of the chicken pieces and 1/2 Ortega chilies.
Next add 1/3 of the grated cheese.
Repeat, ending with tortilla mixture and cheese on top.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour.
This recipe is even better the next day!!! Serves 8.

title: apricot aspic
directions: Drain apricots and reserve juice.
Puree apricots in blender. Combine syrup and jello and heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and gently add all other ingredients.
Mix well and put in 6 1/2-cup mold.
Chill until firm.

title: sensational seafood
directions: Cook rice by directions.
Saute celery, onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Add to cooked rice along with mushrooms, crab, shrimp, pimento, mushroom soup and milk.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: layered shrimp dip
directions: Mix together until smooth.
Spread mixture on large plate or platter, about 1/2 to 1-inch thick.
Cover cheese with bottle of cocktail sauce.
Cover sauce with shrimp, rinsed, drained and deveined.
Surround dip with shredded lettuce or parsley sprigs. Chill before serving with crackers.

title: crispy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in oblong baking dish about 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inches.
Add canned fruit in the bottom and juice.
Mix flour, sugar and egg with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake about 30 minutes at 300° or until golden brown.

title: best ever fish batter
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Dip fish; deep fry.
Tastes like Long John Silvers.

title: esau's pottage
directions: Add rice to boiling, salted water; cover and let cook 15 minutes.
Add onion, oil and lentils.
Boil until lentils are tender.
Should be consistency of mush.
Garnish with parsley and sliced red bell peppers or pimiento.
Serve hot.

title: no cook pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all that together and pour in your pudding and mix all that in your pumpkin and pour all of that on top of your cheese and Cool Whip.

title: hurry-up hamaroni
directions: Prepare mixed vegetables and macaroni separately according to package directions; drain.
Lightly brown onion in oleo in large frying pan.
Add soup and water, stirring to combine.
Stir in ham, vegetables, macaroni, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Cook over medium heat 8 to 10 minutes or until heated through, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican hot dogs
directions: Split each hot dog and fill with onion and grated cheese. Roll tortilla shells around hot dogs.
Place in a row in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour hot chili over all and sprinkle with remaining cheese and onion.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot through and cheese is melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter or margarine.
Add egg yolk, vanilla and flour.
Then mix in potato chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
After baking, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: lemon "n" limeade
directions: Heat and stir sugar and water in a medium sized saucepan just until sugar is dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in lemon and lime juices and pour into a large pitcher.
Mix in ginger ale. Pour into tall glasses filled with ice and sprig with mint.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Use one heaping teaspoon in a small cup or 2 to 3 teaspoons in mug.
Pour boiling water over and voila'-the'!

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Pour cranberry and pineapple juices in 10 cup electric coffeepot.
Put remaining ingredients in basket.
Perk and enjoy.

title: old fashioned banana cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and bake at 350° until done. (Place in two separate baking pans.)
After cooling layers of cake, mash up bananas and spread over one layer of cake; sprinkle a little sugar over bananas.
Place other layer on top of the first and do the same to the second layer.

title: lemon congealed salad(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add lemon juice.
Chill until ready to whip (when it is syrupy or sticks to edge of pan). Whip until foamy.
Add all other ingredients.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Combine in medium bowl the flour, baking powder, salt, softened butter, egg, milk and pudding.
Beat with hand mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Save 6 tablespoons of peach juice and drain peaches.
Cut up and layer in pan on top of mixture.
Combine softened cream cheese (16 ounces), sugar and 6 tablespoons peach juice.
Beat with hand mixer until creamy in texture.
Spoon over peaches.
Top with cinnamon/sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, sugar and margarine and pour over potatoes in Pyrex dish; sprinkle raisins and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: apple dessert
directions: Put sliced apples in buttered 9-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle on top strawberry gelatin.
Mix sugar, flour and margarine until it crumbs.
Sprinkle over apples and gelatin and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Cut meat into cubes.
Remove all fat.
Peel and cut potatoes into cubes.
Peel and cut celery, carrots, onions, bell pepper and mushrooms into bite size pieces.
Place meat and vegetables in a large roasting pan.
Fold in all soups, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and butter.
Do not add water.
Bake in oven at 350° for 2 to 3 hours, uncovered.
Cover pot and bake 1 more hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: easy crabmeat spread
directions: Place cream cheese (whole) on platter.
Mound crabmeat on the cheese.
Pour cocktail sauce over top letting it cover the sides. Serve with crackers.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Spray cookie sheet lightly with no-stick cooking spray.
Drop dough onto sheet by tablespoon.
Bake at 325° for 13 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Keeps in refrigerator for 2 to 3 days, if covered.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Whip the Dream Whip according to directions on package.
Cream the cheese with sugar until smooth.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with pie filling.
Chill.
Makes 1 pie.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Mix rest of ingredients and pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Combine butter/margarine, pecans and flour; mix until crumbly. Pat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.
Blend together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 container Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Prepare pudding according to package instructions.
Place in refrigerator until thickened, about 1/2 hour.
Spread pudding on cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining cream cheese.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: cinnamon croutons
directions: Toss bread cubes with margarine.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes, until crisp and golden.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Mold mixture into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; reduce heat.
Cook until slightly thickened, stirring frequently.
Serve warm.
Makes about 2 2/3 cups of sauce.

title: raisin pineapple pie
directions: Combine oleo and sugar; cream well together.
Add eggs and beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes. Makes a 2-crust pie.

title: favorite cobbler(peaches and blueberries)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and fruits.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and lemon juice.
Pour into a deep 8 1/4 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Sift dry ingredients. Add milk and butter; beat until smooth.
Spread over fruit. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg over batter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chili bean dip
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together in an oven-safe casserole dish. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from oven and place in chafing dish. Serve with chips.
Serves 8.

title: cheesy oven fries
directions: Wash potatoes well and cut each into 8 wedges; set aside.

title: raspberry salad mold
directions: Mix together; place in container and allow to set overnight in refrigerator.
Whip the following day.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Fry bacon.
Chop lettuce and cauliflower.
Layer lettuce, cauliflower, bacon and onion.
Smooth Miracle Whip over top and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish; store overnight.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: delicious crispy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together sugars and butter; add oil, egg and vanilla.
Mix in a separate bowl, sifted flour, salt, soda, corn flakes, oatmeal, coconut and chopped nuts.
Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie pan (sprayed with Pam).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until brown around edges.
Yield:
several dozen.

title: hummingbird cake(warner's favorite!)
directions: Sift dry ingredients into big bowl.
Add all other ingredients and stir until mixed.
Do not beat.
Pour into 3 greased and floured layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: ono hot crab dip
directions: Mix together and bake for 15 minutes at 325°.
Serve warm with cocktail crackers.

title: maggie's tortillas (flour)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Cut shortening into dry ingredients. Add water, a little at a time, to make a medium dough (soft, but not sticky). Knead until smooth.
Let dough rest. Shape into flattened balls and let rest again for about 10 minutes. Roll out on a lightly floured board, turning 1/4 way between each rolling. Brown on a hot, ungreased griddle.

title: cracker spread
directions: Blend cream cheese and Miracle Whip.
Add horseradish and chipped beef.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve on crackers.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except vanilla and margarine, in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until thick, stirring constantly. Add vanilla and margarine; beat and serve over ice cream.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9-inch uncooked pie crust. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mashed potato cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Mix sour milk and baking soda together.
Add all other ingredients and blend well.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with creamy chocolate frosting of your choice.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter, milk and salt in saucepan. Place over heat and bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Blend in peanut butter, oats and vanilla. Blend well. Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper. Let cool. Store in covered container. Keeps well. Makes 40 servings. Preparation time: 0:45.

title: caesar salad
directions: About 1 hour before serving:
In large bowl, combine olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cover bowl; let stand 50 minutes.
Discard garlic.

title: quick drop biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl until well mixed.
Drop onto cookie sheet in heaping spoonfuls.
Makes 8 to 10 biscuits.
Bake in oven at 400° until light brown.

title: sherried beef
directions: Combine all the ingredients (you don't even have to brown the meat) in a large casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours or in a crock-pot on low all day.
(If it cooks a little longer, no harm is done.)
Excellent served over rice or noodles.

title: pudding cake(latiya)
directions: Add milk, butter and sugar in a big pot until boiling.
While boiling, in a separate bowl, add water and cornstarch until smooth (no lumps).
After smoothing, pour into boiling pot until mixture thickens, while pot is not boiling.

In the meantime, you will have to slice pound cake and spread it 1/2-inch on the tray. Then after done, pour your pot of pudding and spread on tray on top of cake also, then sprinkle your cinnamon all over.
Chill and slice.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Mix raw ground beef (I use chuck) with other ingredients and cook over low heat for 45 minutes.
Serve while hot.
I freeze leftovers in small portions.

title: no egg pumpkin pies
directions: Line 2 pie plates with pastry.
Put pumpkin in bowl; add sugar, flour, salt and baking powder and mix together.
Then stir in the spices and the milk.
Fill the pie plates and bake in a hot oven to a rich golden brown color.

title: white pizza dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together using 3/4 of cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with French bread.

title: cheddar hash browns
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°. The last 1/2 hour, add corn flakes to top.

title: honey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and store up to 2 weeks in glass container in refrigerator.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all together for 1 to 2 minutes. Pour in 2 large or 5 small loaf pans, greased. Bake at 350° for 1 hour (top will crack). Cool and remove from pans. Poke holes in top with fork.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt together Milky Way candy bars and 1 stick margarine.
Set aside.
Cream together 2 sticks butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and salt.
Add alternately buttermilk, soda and flour, beating after each addition.
Beat well.
Add Milky Way mixture and pecans.
Pour into prepared angel food cake pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Not suitable for layer cake.

title: corn pudding
directions: Put into blender ingredients, except corn.
Blend for abut 10 seconds.
Stop blender, then add to mixture in it the corn.
Blend for about 10 seconds more.
Pour into greased baking dish or casserole.
Bake for 45 minutes uncovered, at 375° or according to what your oven requires for the mixture to be "set" and pleasantly brown.
(I like to use a Pyrex dish so that I can watch to be sure the bottom part does not get too brown.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: super bowl sunday supper
directions: Pre-Kick Off:
Brown beef with pepper.
Drain.
Stir in onion mix, chili powder and tomato sauce.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese and chili.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips until well blended.
(Strain salsa, if desired.)
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips and/or fresh vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.
This is quick, easy and very good.

title: benny's poor man pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar.
While mixing, beat in eggs.
Add vanilla and other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into pie shell. Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Combine all the ingredients except the chips and cheese. Add to the browned hamburger. Arrange chips in the bottom of a baking dish, top with half the hamburger mixture and cheese. Repeat the layers and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix together the flour and salt and add the cold water.
Beat until smooth and gradually add the hot water.
Boil until clear. Beat until smooth. Add food colorings. Store in jars.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine.
Cook over medium heat for a few minutes.
Pour sauce over meatballs.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: apple stack cake
directions: Add flour to other ingredients to make a stiff dough, enough to roll out.
Roll dough until thin layer.
Put in round pan to bake for about 15 minutes.
Bake at 450°.
Cool.
Put together in a stack with apple filling (makes 4 or 5 layers).

title: quick cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter or margarine in an 8-inch square pan.
Mix sugar, flour and baking powder.
Combine dry ingredients with milk.
Pour batter into pan of melted butter. Pour pie filling over the dough.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: rice chex treats
directions: Cook syrup and sugar until clear.
Take off stove and add peanut butter; blend in well.
Add vanilla and stir.
Pour over Chex and mix until all is coated.
Drop on wax paper by the tablespoonful.
Cool.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: backyard garden casserole
directions: Place sliced eggplant in one layer on baking sheet.
Brush with oil and broil for a few minutes.
Oil a baking dish, 8 x 12-inches.
Arrange eggplant slices, slightly overlapping.

title: vidalia onion cornbread
directions: In a bowl, mix Jiffy mix, egg and milk.
Spread in bottom of an 8-inch pan.
Set aside.
Saut sliced Vidalia onion in butter until onions have a glazed look.
Add sour cream, salt and half of cheese to onion mix.
Spread evenly over cornbread mix in pan. Sprinkle remaining cheese over mixture.
Bake at 325° to 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate candy bar dessert
directions: Mix cookie crumbs, 1/4 cup of sugar and margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press firmly into bottom of pan.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Beat cream cheese and remaining 1/4 cup sugar in medium bowl until smooth.
Gently stir in half the Cool Whip.
Spread evenly over crust.
Sprinkle chopped candy bars over cream cheese layer.
Pour milk into large bowl.
Add both pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute.
Pour over candy bar layer.
Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding layer.
Refrigerate 2 hours until set.
Cut into squares. Store leftover dessert in refrigerator.
Makes 15 to 18 servings.

title: mexicali pork chops
directions: Trim fat form pork chops and cook trimmings in skillet and remove.
Cook chops until brown.
Remove chops to salt and pepper, then add green peppers and onions and cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, corn, rice, water and chilies.
Add salt and a few dashes of hot sauce.
Bring to a boil, then put mixture into a cake pan and place pork chops on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Scald milk in large pan and add sugar.
In bowl place eggs, cornstarch and evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Add to heated milk the sugar mixture.
Stir until mixture boils.
Remove from heat. Add rice and vanilla.
Pour into large bowl and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Add raisins if desired.

title: chili corn dog casserole
directions: Evenly spread chili beans in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Evenly space wieners atop of chili in dish.
Prepare corn bread and pour over layered ingredients.
Try to seal corn bread to edges of the dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese over corn bread.
Bake time and temperature called for in your corn bread recipe or package instructions.
Cheese is optional.

title: scotch tea cookies
directions: In saucepan heat sugar and butter until butter melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oats, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Spoon into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in order listed. Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix over filling. Drizzle butter over top. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm. Serve warm with Cool Whip.

title: german sauerbraten
directions: Combine salt and ginger; rub over roast. Place in a deep glass bowl. In a saucepan, combine water, vinegar, onions, sugar, pickling spices, peppercorns, cloves and
bay leaves; bring to a boil. Pour over roast; turn to coat. Cover and refrigerate for 2 days, turning twice a day.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Bake pie shell 5 to 6 minutes at 400°.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Mix well with a fork.
Place in 2-quart saucepan. Add margarine.
Beat egg yolks and mix with evaporated milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickens and bubbles.
It burns easily, so stir constantly. May take 7 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; stir well.
Pour into crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add cream of tartar.
May add 1/2 cup sugar.
Place on pie.
Brown in oven for 1 minute.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook veggies.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix cheese, mayonnaise, celery and onions.
Spread mixture over the veggies. Crumble Ritz crackers over veggies.
Melt margarine and pour over. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes in oven or ten minutes in microwave.
It's much better in oven.

title: continental peas
directions: In 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook, covered, on medium heat until tender, 6 to 10 minutes.

title: sour milk chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and egg.
Add soda to sour milk and add to mixture alternately with flour.

title: shoofly pie
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon, cloves, ginger and nutmeg.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender or two knives until mixture resembles coarse meal.

title: mexican soup
directions: In Dutch oven, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion tender.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients (do not drain). Stir together and simmer about 1 hour.
Top servings with grated cheese and Fritos.
If too thick, add V-8 juice.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix together sugar and butter.
In another small bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar and butter mixture. Add milk and mix well.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish. Drain cherries and reserve juice.
Pour cherries over batter; sprinkle sugar over cherries (depending on tartness of cherries). Pour 1/2 cup cherry juice over all.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the three packages of broccoli for 5 minutes in salted water.
In large casserole dish, put layers of broccoli, sliced onion, sliced water chestnuts, grated cheese and mushroom soup. Heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Drain and mash the eggplant.
Add beaten egg, sugar, flour and baking powder.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon of mixture into hot corn oil. Remove when golden brown.
Drain.

title: garlic potatoes(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine all ingredients; place in a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour and 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: spinach maria
directions: You can use frozen spinach. Be sure there is no water in spinach.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into small balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Cook potatoes; mash well. Let cool. Add powdered sugar. Make a dough of the potatoes and sugar. Put into freezer for 30 minutes. Work dough again. Roll out as thin as possible. Spread with peanut butter. Roll up like a log. Cut into slices.

title: baked new potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes in a baking dish.
Combine butter and remaining ingredients.
Pour over potatoes and turn potatoes to coat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes or until tender.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and chopped onion. Mix with other ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes in greased casserole dish.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Boil macaroni and drain.
In a 5 quart saucepan combine meat, macaroni, chili beans, tomato sauce, tomato paste, chopped onion and Tabasco sauce to taste.
Simmer on low heat until consistency desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and toss with stuffing mix.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl; add half of stuffing mix. Pour into greased casserole and top with remaining stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Freezes nicely.

title: grandma's icebox cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and cut mixture in half.
Then form into two long rolls, two-inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and freeze.
Slice thin and bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: meatballs in sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except the chili sauce and grape jelly.
Roll into one-inch balls.
Place in pan and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: waldorf supreme salad
directions: Sprinkle sugar and lemon juice over apples.
Add celery, pecans, cherries and raisins.
Fold salad dressing into Cool Whip. Gradually fold into apple mixture.
Chill.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter.
Add soup, water, onion and mushrooms.
Cook in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour in mixture.
Then place chicken breasts on top.
Salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry dessert
directions: Mix the cranberries, 1/2 cup sugar and chopped nuts.
Put the cranberry mixture in the bottom of a greased and floured 9 x 11-inch pan.

title: iced tea
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Put frozen strawberries in saucepan over low heat.
Add hot water.
Bring this to a boil.
Remove from heat and add the jello. Stir.
Pour into a dish and put into refrigerator.

title: white christmas cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 2 cookie sheets.
In bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter with sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla. Gradually beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate, nuts and raisins.

title: sour cream lemon tarts
directions: Whisk sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan to mix. Whisk in milk, egg yolks and lemon juice until smooth. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil, stirring constantly, for 30 seconds or until transparent and very thick. Remove from heat. Add lemon peel and butter; stir until melts. Cover surface with plastic wrap to prevent a skim from forming. Cool to room temperature. Fold in sour cream until blended. Spoon into tart shells. Cover loosely and refrigerate at least 4 hours or up to 2 days. Garnish with whipped cream and lemon slices.

title: cranberry apple casserole
directions: In a large bowl, toss together cranberries, apples and sugar. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of cocoa and red food coloring.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix salt and vanilla with buttermilk and add alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Mix soda and vinegar; fold in mixture.
Do not beat after last addition.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: *blueberry delight
directions: Make graham cracker crust according to the directions on the graham cracker box.
Beat the cream cheese and sugar with an electric mixer until smooth and creamy.
Make 1 envelope of Dream Whip according to the package directions.
Combine Dream Whip mixture and cream cheese-sugar mixture together in a large bowl with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Spoon filling into crust and top with blueberry filling.
Chill until ready to serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Tear tinfoil into large square sections.
Place a hamburger patty in the center; lay potatoes on top and onions next.
Fold the corners together like making a sack.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes or until hamburger is done.

title: pasta vegetable salad
directions: Cook macaroni to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain; rinse with cold water.
In large bowl, combine cooked macaroni, zucchini, broccoli, onions, mushrooms, artichokes and salad dressing.
Toss gently.
Cover; refrigerate at least 3 hours to blend flavors.
Just before serving, stir in tomatoes and avocado.
Makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in a large bowl until dissolved.
Stir in measured liquid.
Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours.

title: meat balls and noodles
directions: Cook noodles as directed; set aside.
Mix meat, onion, salt, pepper, egg and crumbled bread.
Mix well.
Form into balls and put into saucepan with small amount of oil.
Cook until done; drain.
Add mushroom soup and sour cream.
Cover and let cook until all is mixed well.
Add noodles and mix well.
If too dry, can add some milk.

title: overnight lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and salt; cook several minutes, stirring frequently.
Drain fat.
In large mixing bowl, combine spaghetti sauce, water, oregano, pepper and sugar.

title: creamy butter frosting
directions: Add instant coffee to sugar.
Stir ingredients.

title: hot stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cook sausage, drain.
Save drippings.
Saute onions in 1 tablespoon of drippings.
Add sausage to onions.
Add cream cheese until melted.
Knead with hands.
Fill mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Scrub potatoes well.
Cut lengthwise into 6 wedges the size and shape of dill pickle spears and dry with paper towel.
In large bowl toss potatoes with oil.
Place skin side down on baking sheet lined with foil.
Dust potatoes with seasonings.
Bake 30 minutes or until fork-tender.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and make a well in center. Combine eggs, oil and strawberries, mixing well. Add this mixture to the dry ingredients, stirring just enough to moisten dry ingredients. Stir in nuts. Pour into 6 greased 6 x 3 x 2-inch foil pans or 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes for small pans or 1 hour for large pans. Let cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: crumb cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Add shortening and make crumbs for top.
Save 1/2 cup crumbs.
Combine egg, soda and milk.
Stir well.
Add to first mixture.
Add flavoring.
Put crumbs on top and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well.
Add milk and wafers; stir.
Add nuts, raisins and coconut and stir.
Bake in greased tube pan at 275° to 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: savory cabbage rolls
directions: Combine rice, beef, onion, salt, pepper and drained tomatoes that have been cut-up into chunks; mix well.
Steam cabbage leaves for 3 minutes or until just limp.
Spoon meat mixture onto leaves. Roll each leaf around meat, turning ends under.
Place in large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Pour tomato sauce and remaining tomato juice over rolls.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove rolls to warm platter.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: In a saucepan, saute garlic in butter until tender.
Add the next eight ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and set aside.
On the grill, place chicken over low heat and grill for about 30 minutes or until cooked through. (To speed up this process, can parboil the chicken before placing on the grill).
Baste with the sauce.
Grill about 20 minutes longer, basting and turning the
chicken several times.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions together until tender.
While squash is still warm, add cream cheese, crumbled, and oleo, cut in small pieces.
Save enough oleo to dot on top.
Place half cracker crumbs on top.
Add eggs and place in a greased casserole.
Cover with remaining cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake in 325° oven until set and crackers are slightly brown.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine melted cheese and milk.
Add potatoes, vegetables, ham and onion.
Add dash of pepper; mix well.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan and cover.
Bake for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover; sprinkle with cheese and crackers.
Bake for 5 minutes.

title: butterscotch pecan rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add butter, salt and sugar.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add yeast mixture to milk mixture, then add egg and 2 cups of flour.
Add and mix remainder of flour.
Cover and set in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Remove and let it get to room temperature.
Knead.
Roll out on floured board.
Spread with butter; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and cut in 1-inch slices.
Put 1/2 cup melted butter in a baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Sprinkle brown sugar and pecan halves over butter.
Place slightly apart in pan.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Immediately invert pan onto a serving plate.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Stir lemonade into condensed milk. Fold in Cool Whip and spoon into baked pie shell. Freeze. (Limeade may be substituted for lemonade.)

title: honey yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine 2 1/2 cups flour and salt in food processor bowl; add yeast mixture.
Process until blended; melt butter and combine with honey and eggs.
Process until well blended.
Add 1 additional cup of flour; process until blended. Add remaining flour 1/4 cup at a time, processing in between. Turn dough into greased bowl and let rise 1 hour.
Punch dough down and shape into 24 rolls and place into greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Let rise 25 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter over baked rolls.

title: walnut cake
directions: Beat eggs until blended; add sugar, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Blend.
Stir in nuts.
Add hot milk slowly and stir. Mix all ingredients together good and quick.
Pour batter in a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake(yield: 10-12 pieces)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.

Mix dry ingredients in food processor. Add cheese and process until cheese is blended into dry ingredients (cheese will appear as flecks in the flour mixture). Place dry mixture in mixing bowl and add mixture of buttermilk and oil, mixing in buttermilk to moisten flour.
Turn mixture onto floured surface.
Pat out dough into 1-inch high oval and cut biscuits with biscuit cutter or glass.
Place biscuits on well-greased 14 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake for 20 to 22 minutes at 425°.

title: bacon cheddar ranch dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended. Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: company jello salad
directions: Step 1:
Dissolve 1 package red jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Pour into dish for first layer.
Let congeal.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken with onions and celery. Pick off bone. Cook noodles in broth. Mix everything together and put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: puffy cheese souffle
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt and pepper. Remove from heat.
Gradually cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Gradually add sauce to slightly beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Carefully fold the cheese mixture and pour into casserole (1 1/2-quart).
Bake in pan of hot water at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pasta with fresh tuna
directions: Place 1/4 cup of the oil and the onion in a large skillet. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until the onion is very soft, about 10 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, 1/2 teaspoon of the salt and 1/4 teaspoon of the pepper.
Cook over moderate heat, partially covered, until the juices thicken to form a sauce, about 5 minutes.
Remove from the heat and set aside.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken into sheet pan.
Add chicken broth, cream of chicken
soup, mixed vegetables and onion.
Mix the flour, milk and
margarine;
pour
over top of first ingredients and cook at 425° for 30 minutes.
(Serves 6.)

title: spiced carrots
directions: Prepare carrots and slice into 1/2-inch thick round slices. Heat vinegar, olive oil and peppers.
Put carrots in strainer and place in boiling vinegar 10 seconds.
Pack carrots in pint jars. Strain vinegar.
Pour over carrots and seal.

title: swiss noodles
directions: Parboil elbow noodles.
Lightly cover bottom of a glass Pyrex pie dish with olive oil.
Mix remainder of oil with garlic (minced) and parsley and oregano with the parboiled elbows.
Cover Pyrex dish with elbow noodles, placing a layer of Swiss cheese over it, continuing doing same until the dish is filled.
The last layer should be Swiss cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese is slightly browned and bubbling.

title: 14 carat fig cake
directions: Drain crushed pineapple, reserving juice.
Place figs, water and vanilla in blender and puree.
Lightly beat together eggs and egg whites.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon into a mixing bowl.
Stir to blend dry ingredients.
Add pureed figs, egg/whites mixture, carrots, pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Stir until blended well.
Turn into 13 x 9-inch baking pan sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done in the center. While cake cools, blend together powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons of reserved pineapple juice.
Drizzle over cake for glaze.

title: creamy crunchy chicken rice bake
directions: Combine Cheez Whiz and hot rice.
Add chicken, peas and half the onion rings.
Mix lightly.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with remaining onion rings and bake 5 minutes longer until lightly browned.

title: favorite hawaiian dessert
directions: Mix cake batter according to directions on box.
Pour into 2 greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool completely.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, olives, pimentos, and nuts. Spread mixture on tortillas; top with ham and roll up tight like a jelly roll. Chill and slice with an electric knife. Serve with a toothpick. Keep refrigerated and covered until ready to serve.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Toss together lettuce, onion, oranges and cashews.
Mix together thoroughly oil, sugar, vinegar, lemon juice, garlic and Heinz 57.
Toss dressing with salad or serve on the side.

title: cottage cheese lime gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve in boiling water the lemon and lime flavored gelatins. Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Add cottage cheese, crushed pineapple, mayonnaise and evaporated milk.
Chill until set.

title: butterscotch brownies supreme
directions: Mix melted butter with other ingredients.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for exactly 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares while warm.
Makes 16 or more.

title: brownie fudge squares
directions: Melt margarine in a small saucepan.
Add cocoa and mix well. Set aside.
Combine eggs and sugar in a large bowl.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add chocolate mixture and beat until just blended.
Mix in pecans.
Pour into a greased and floured 16 x 11-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Trim as much outside fat from pork chop as possible.
Combine sauerkraut, mustard, cream, sugar, salt and pepper.

Place mixture in baking dish large enough to fit chops in one layer. Dip chops in seasoned flour and thoroughly shake off excess. Heat oil in 12-inch skillet. When hot, saute chops over medium heat, about 2 to 3 minutes per side, until golden brown. Season lightly with salt and pepper.
Place on sauerkraut. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: banana split muffins
directions: Mix together the softened ice cream and flour until flour has "disappeared."
Add strawberries and banana pieces and stir five times.
The batter will turn pink.
Fill batter into pre-greased tins.
Place chocolate chips on top of each muffin.
Place in oven and bake at 375° until done and slightly brown on top.
Let cool 15 minutes before removing from tins and tasting.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In
a
large
pot,
boil chicken breast in about 6 cups water until
done.
Remove chicken breast, and while broth is still boiling,
add spaghetti and cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain spaghetti; reserving	broth.	Remove	chicken
from
bone and dice.
In large
skillet,
saute onions and celery in butter. Add
soup, chicken, pimentos and about 1/2 cup broth, spaghetti, salt and pepper to taste.
Place in casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat on low speed with an electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Spoon into a greased and floured 10 inch bunt pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 5-10 minutes, or until a wooden toothpick interested in the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add sugar, egg, butter and vanilla; beat smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup of walnuts and pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Remove from oven and immediately arrange marshmallows, remaining walnuts and chocolate chips over top.
Return pan to oven for 2 minutes or until chocolate is softened.
Remove from oven.
Swirl chocolate over marshmallows and walnuts with a spatula.
Cool until chocolate is set.
Cut into bars.
Enjoy!

title: baked lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken in a lightly greased baking pan.
Combine all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Combine salad dressing mix with sour cream.
Stir to blend. Chill or heat to desired serving temperature.
Do not boil.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat together the eggs, salt and baking powder.
Then add flour slowly until done.
If too thick, add one more egg.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: In a bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Shape cheese mixture into ball.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap or foil. Refrigerate 6 hours.

title: cornbread(from the files of louella scott williams)
directions: This will need about 25 minutes of cooking time.
You can omit the cheese if you like.

title: peanut butter jelly bar
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in margarine. Mix until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Stir until smooth.
Reserve half.
Press half onto a small 13 x 9-inch cookie sheet.
Spread grape jelly evenly over dough.
Sprinkle 1 cup peanut butter chips over jelly.
Crumble remaining dough over jelly and chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or lightly browned.
Remove from oven immediately.
Sprinkle remaining chips over top.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: kaffeekachin
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add half in well-greased pan, then add half of the Streusel Filling.
Pour in rest of batter and add rest of filling on top.
Bake in 6 x 10-inch or 8-inch square pan, well-greased.
Bake in a 375° oven.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, salad dressing and mustard together.
Pour over cornbread and vegetables and mix together.
Add sugar if desired.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Mix sauce with chili powder, oregano and salt; set aside. Soften tortillas in oil.
Line pan with softened tortillas.
Let tortillas lap over edge of pan.
Pour layer of cooked meat on top of tortillas.
Put in a layer of green onions and cheese.
Fold sides of tortillas and put more tortillas on top.
Cover with more green onions and cheese.
Pour sauce in.
Leave enough to pour on very top.
Put layer of tortillas on top.
Cover with cheese.
Pour on sauce.
Put in oven until cheese melts.

title: good salad
directions: Mix all together; add dry Jell-O as comes from box.
Place in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain the macaroni.
Add the desired amount of green pepper, the carrots and olives.
Mix the mayonnaise, milk, sugar, and vinegar.
Add to the macaroni mixture and let set overnight. It will keep up to two weeks in the refrigerator.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Pour into covered container and put in refrigerator. Rising takes place in refrigerator. Use as needed.

title: easy corn bread
directions: *Or can be made without eggs.

title: barbecue pork and beef sandwiches
directions: About 8 hours before serving, combine beef for stew, pork cubes, onions, green peppers, tomato paste, brown sugar, cider vinegar, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard. Cover; cook on high in crock-pot for 8 hours.
Stir with fork until meat is shredded.
Line sub rolls with Boston lettuce; fill with meat mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped tomato.
Makes 12 sandwiches.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine sugar, vanilla, eggs, applesauce, nutmeg and milk. Break bread into small pieces.
Put into mix and mix well.
Melt butter; put into deep 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until golden brown at 350° or 300°.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Stir the dry seasoning mix into the meat.
Combine meat and vegetables in a large salad bowl. Just before serving, toss with dressing and corn chips.
Makes ten servings.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes longer, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal.
Stir until well coated.

title: fried cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
Soak in vinegar for 5 minutes. Drain on paper towel.
Mix flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag. Heat oil in frying skillet and fry cucumbers after coating with flour mixture.

title: nut torte
directions: Melt butter in a large, flat pan, 11 x 16-inch.
Preheat oven to 275°.
Mix together the brown sugar, salt, soda, eggs, flour and nuts.
Pour batter over the butter.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
The batter will spread as it cooks.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: chicken elegante
directions: Saute in butter the celery and onion.
Set aside.
Cut, bone and cut into pieces the chicken breasts. Mix with sour cream, mushroom soup, mushrooms, lemon pepper and pepper.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 8in graham cracker crusts. Chill overnight if possible.

title: punch(red or yellow)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill.
You may add ginger ale.

title: tennessee biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening. Add yeast and buttermilk.
Mix with spoon and roll into a ball.
Cover tightly in a large bowl and place in refrigerator until cool and ready to use.
Take out as needed. Roll out with rolling pin from 1/4 to 3/4-inch thick.
Brush with melted butter and bake in oven at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding with milk until thick.
Add cream cheese, condensed milk and vanilla until well blended.
Fold in half the Cool Whip (leave some for the top).
In a large bowl, layer wafers, bananas and then pudding mix.
Top with the rest of the Cool Whip; refrigerate.

title: beef and macaroni
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Pour cooked macaroni over meat.
Add catsup, salt and pepper; stir.
Add soup; mix thoroughly.
Top with cheese.
Put in a 450° oven until cheese melts.
Yields 6 servings.

title: strawberry dessert pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Mold into 9-inch pie plate.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding vinegar, sugar and vanilla gradually.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Pour into cracker crust. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Place strawberries on top of pie; cover with whipped cream and walnuts. Garnish with strawberries.
Chill overnight.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: easy ovenburgers
directions: Combine meat and seasonings.
Add crumbs and egg; mix well. Shape into patties.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Heat 4 tablespoons oil in large skillet over high heat.
Add potatoes, green pepper, onion and garlic.
Quickly cook until potatoes are lightly brown, turning mixture frequently.
Remove from heat.
Stir in corned beef, mustard, salt, pepper and yogurt. Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine cheese, bread crumbs and remaining 1 tablespoon of oil in small bowl.
Toss until well mixed.
Sprinkle evenly over corned beef mixture.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until browned and bubbling.
Serves 4.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and both sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and peanut butter and beat well.

title: pimiento cheese
directions: Combine cream cheese and pimiento. Stir well. Add mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Cover and chill.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In large bowl place chocolate chips, butter, chopped nuts and tsp. vanilla. Melt over double boiler 10 large marshmallows and 1 teaspoon of water. Boil for 5 to 10 minutes the sugar and evaporated milk, but do not scorch the milk.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Cut apples into bite-size pieces.
Stir in other ingredients. Save 1/2 crushed peanuts to top.

title: beef brisket
directions: Cover and cook brisket and ingredients at least 6 hours.

title: easy cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce; stir well.
Add orange juice, rind (finely chopped), and pineapple. Chill until set.
Yields 10 - 12 servings.

title: puffy pizza
directions: Cut biscuits in 4, stir in 1 c. sauce and 2 c. cheese and other ingredients. Put remaining cheese and sauce on top, in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.

title: summer delight(sugar-free)
directions: Mix pudding as directed and pour into the cooled crust. Spread Cool Whip over top.

title: streusel filled coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening. Beat egg, milk and vanilla together; mix with dry ingredients just until all is moist (do not beat).
Put in pan; sprinkle topping mixture over all.

title: chicken cheese soup
directions: Saute mushrooms, celery and onions in 2 tablespoons margarine. Add other ingredients except cheeses and mix well.
Bring all to boiling.
Add cheese; lower temperature and stir constantly (to keep from sticking and scorching) until cheese melts.

title: cherry winks
directions: Mix Crisco, egg, sugar, vanilla, milk and flour, then add 1/2 cup raisins and nuts.
Make dough into small balls.
Roll in corn flake crumbs.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cook at 375° until lightly browned.
Place 1/4 cherry on top of each cookie.

title: chocolate almond crunch pie
directions: Prepare pudding.
Pour in shell and chill 4 hours (at least). Chop almonds coarsely and toast at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes. Combine butter and sugar in pan at low temperature, until butter is melted.
Stir in nuts.
Remove from heat and stir until cool. Sprinkle on pie.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box, folding apples in.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan and bake according to directions on box.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, sour cream and lemon juice.
Spread on baked cake and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: magic butter rolls
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add chopped onion, then milk and egg, beaten together.
Drop by small spoonfuls into boiling deep fat.
They will float when done.
Drain on brown paper.
Serves 8.

title: slaw mix
directions: Mix vinegar and sugar. Stir good and let set for 5 minutes. Add mayo and mix well. Use as mix for slaw or a salad dressing.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add the following:
whole cranberries, crushed pineapple, celery and nuts.

title: harvest stew
directions: Mix everything together and put in Dutch oven.
Bake 5 hours at 225° to 250°.
Do not take lid off while baking.
This may also be cooked in crock-pot.

title: elmarie moore's sweet and sour shrimp
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and vinegar; cook until clear over medium heat.
Add hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and red and green peppers.
Add pineapple chunks with syrup.
Simmer together 10 minutes.
Add boiled shrimp.

title: beef stew
directions: Cover in Dutch oven and bake 3 hours, stirring twice, until meat is tender.

title: french silk pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar, unsweetened chocolate and vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, beating 2 minutes after each egg. Put in baked pie shell. Chill 2-3 hours before serving. Add Cool Whip or shaved chocolate, if desired.

title: sweet and sour ham
directions: Cut ham into bite-size strips.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, stir together ham, pineapple tidbits and mandarin orange sections and water chestnuts.
Microcook, covered, on 100% power (High) for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until heated through, stirring once.
Let stand, covered, while preparing sauce.

title: very strawberry pie
directions: In saucepan, crush 2 cups berries; add cornstarch and sugar. Cook, stirring until mixture boils.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Fold in lemon juice and the 2 cups of halved berries.
Pour into baked crust; chill.
Serve with whipping cream.
Double recipe for large pie pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done with onion, celery, salt and pepper. Remove chicken from broth and cook until desired tenderness.
When chicken is cool, remove meat from bones.
When spaghetti is done, place in baking dish.
Toss chicken and spaghetti together.
Add 1 1/2 cups of chicken broth.
Put Cheddar cheese on top.
Place in oven at 350° and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: german chocolate fudge
directions: Combine chocolate morsels, sweet chocolate and marshmallow cream in a large bowl.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, butter, milk and salt in a heavy skillet.
Bring mixture to a boil; boil 6 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: In an oblong glass baking dish, line the bottom of the dish with wafers.
Cook pudding and cool slightly.
Pour half of the pudding over the wafers.
Then add a second layer of wafers.
Then add a second layer of wafers and another layer of pudding.
Let pudding set for 1 hour in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with chopped nuts over the Cool Whip.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in egg, then add molasses.
Sift flour and all dry ingredients together. Gradually add flour to other ingredients.
Blend for 3 to 4 minutes.
Shape into balls the size of a quarter.
Dip into sugar. Place on cookie sheet sugar side up.
With finger, add a drop of water to each if you like cracked cookie look.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten eggs and stir in drained pineapple.
Stir in bread pieces; mix well.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: forget-me-not cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites and salt.
Then add slowly the sugar.
Beat to meringue consistency.
Fold in vanilla, nuts and chips.
Drop on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Put cookies in oven and turn oven off!
Leave in oven overnight.
Do not open the oven to peek.

title: seasoned coating mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Place in covered container and store in cool place.
For chicken, dip pieces in water and shake in plastic bag with coating mix.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 60 minutes, uncovered.

title: frikadeller(meat dumplings)
directions: Soak the bread crumbs in the cream.
Combine the veal, pork, crumb mixture, egg yolks, salt and pepper.
Beat with a fork. Using teaspoons, shape the mixture into small meatballs.
In a large saucepan, dissolve the bouillon cubes into boiling water. Add the meatballs a few at a time.
Simmer over moderate heat about 5 minutes.
Remove with a slotted spoon.
Drain on paper towels. Keep warm.
Serve with a dill, lemon, tomato or caper sauce, if desired.

title: "potato thing"
directions: Boil potatoes in jacket (cool completely and grate).
Shred Cheddar cheese.
Mix grated potatoes with the sour cream and chopped fresh green onions; salt and pepper to desired taste. Cube stick of oleo and place on top of the mixed ingredients.
Top with shredded cheese.
Heat in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into graham crust.
Cool in refrigerator 2 hours before serving.

title: 7 can soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
In a large pot, add beef to remaining ingredients.
Simmer on low heat for 1 hour.
Any vegetables can be used according to individual tastes.
Adjust seasonings to taste.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook pasta until tender.
Add onion, tomato and cucumber.

title: beef pepper steak
directions: Preheat oil in electric skillet, uncovered, at 325°.
Add meat and brown.
Remove meat; add onion and green peppers.
Cook until tender.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake 30 to 40 minutes in low oven until firm in middle. Salt after cooking, if desired.

title: baked squash surprise(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender.
Drain and mash.
Season to taste.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix stuffing and oleo.
Reserve half stuffing.
Put balance of stuffing in squash mixture.
Line large casserole with reserved stuffing.
Pour in squash mixture.
Add balance of stuffing on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
May prepare the day before.
Bake when needed.
Freeze well.

title: creamy corn
directions: Cut tops off kernels of corn and scrape remaining pulp and milk out of the kernels.
Heat butter in a saucepan and add corn. Cook for 3 to 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in the cream and heat 10 minutes more until corn is tender, stirring constantly.

title: aroma punch
directions: Place orange and lemon peels in a small pan.
Add cinnamon sticks and whole cloves.
Pour water over the fruit and spices and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat until liquid is at a low boil. Check pan occasionally to make sure the water doesn't boil away.

title: snappy sauce
directions: Stir and cook until mixed well.
Use with chicken wings, cocktail sausages or ?
