title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together at once.
Put in pie shell.
Bake pie in hot oven (450°) for 12 minutes, and then reduce heat to 350° and bake around 30 minutes longer, or until an inserted knife comes out clean.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground beef in Dutch oven.
Drain fat.
Return pan to medium-low heat and add remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: *Beef can be leftover roast or leftover hamburgs.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together with a fork.
In a separate dish, beat together the last 3 ingredients.
Combine flour mixture with wet mixture (using fork) only until all ingredients are moistened.
Mold dough into a ball.
Chill at least 15 minutes before making crusts.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 5 single crusts.

title: gumbo
directions: Using 12 to 15-quart pot, boil chicken in 1/2 pot of water. Remove from water to cool when done. Wash and string celery; chop stalk and leaves. Wash and chop onions. Drop celery and onions in water that chicken was cooked in. Cut sausage into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces; quarter each piece. Add sausage, crawfish and shrimp to pot. While this is cooking, debone chicken; cut cross grain into small pieces and set aside. Add oregano and okra to pot. Melt shortening in iron skillet. Stir in flour and brown until almost black. Add to pot. Add chicken and cook
until vegetables are soft. Spoon out excess grease.

title: milk chocolate brownie cake(serves 16)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease jelly roll pan with shortening. Heat in saucepan, stirring a few times, margarine or butter, water and cocoa.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour batter into the pan (batter will be thin).
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Frost cake when cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 30 -35 minutes at 350 degrees, uncovered.

title: tomato-cucumber marinade
directions: Blend the salad oil, vinegar, cheese, garlic, salt, sugar and pepper; shake well.
Pour dressing over sliced tomatoes and sliced cucumber.
Let stand about 30 minutes at room temperature.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter, add
sugar;
mix
well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour,	milk, alternate flour and milk starting with flour and ending
with
flour.
Add vanilla last.
Grease and flour tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: chicken and tomato sauce
directions: Boil chicken long enough so skins can be easily removed, about 15 minutes.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour or until chicken is done.
Sauce is good served over rice.

title: microwave pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla; stir in pecans.
Pour into prepared crust.
Cook at Medium for 7 to 9 minutes or until pie is set.
Let stand until cool.
Garnish, if desired, with sweetened whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: christmas cheese balls(makes three 1 ounce balls)
directions: Mix well; shape into 3 large balls and refrigerate.
Take out 1 hour before serving.

title: quiche lorraine(great for breakfast or brunch!)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Combine eggs, half and half and seasonings.
Beat until well blended. Crumble bacon into bottom of pastry shell and then sprinkle with cheese.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 4 servings.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, turmeric and mustard seed.
Pour mixture over cukes in jug and put lid on and place in refrigerator.

title: amy's double stuff potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 350° for 1 hour (let cool).
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop potato out to make shells.
Mix potatoes with all ingredients (1/2 cup Cheddar cheese).
Fill shells with potato mixture and top with the other 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and serve.

title: apricot chews
directions: Mix all together.
Stir well and frequently.
Drop on well-greased or Teflon cookie sheet in bite-sized servings.
Bake 20 minutes at 300° and remove immediately from pan.
Makes 6 dozen.
Freezes beautifully.
This recipe is a confection that may be served as a candy, cookie, tea cookie or is a marvelous gift for friends.

title: oyster stew(easy and delicious)
directions: Melt butter in the top of a double boiler.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Heat, over medium heat, until oysters float on top and soup is steaming.

title: ted's salad
directions: Combine the mayonnaise, red wine vinegar and Sweet 'N Low. Mix thoroughly with veggies and meat mixture.

title: nougat bars
directions: In double boiler, melt butter and marshmallows; remove from heat.
Fold in cereal, nuts, coconut and salt.
Turn into buttered 8-inch square pan.
With hands protected by wax paper, pat out evenly in pan.
Pour over top 4 ounces sweet chocolate, melted. Spread it in thin layers with rubber spatula.
Chill until set. Cut into bars.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg, parsley, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce and form into balls.
Melt shortening and brown meatballs.
Heat chili sauce and grape jelly until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped apples
directions: Pare, core and slice apples.
Place in a greased casserole dish and add the cinnamon, salt, lemon juice and water.
Work the sugar, flour and butter together until crumb-like.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese log
directions: Let stand at room temperature until soft. Mix and put in plastic wrap in fridge for a few hours. Roll in log shape and roll in chopped nuts.

title: chicken and mushroom soup
directions: Cut up chicken and cook in salt and pepper until meat is almost done.
Add celery (cut up) and green pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes; add can of mushroom soup.
Cover 5 minutes more.
Cook until rice is done.
Separately follow instructions on rice box, preferably Uncle Ben's wild rice.
Serve chicken over rice.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add enough water to make 1 cup; boil. Dissolve Jell-O and let cool slightly.
Dissolve gelatin in small amount of cold water.
Pour 1 1/4 cups boiling water over the cream cheese and cut marshmallows.
Beat slightly to dissolve cheese.
Cool mixture, then add pineapple and nuts.
Mix lightly and congeal.
Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.

title: prune bread
directions: Soak prunes overnight in water.
Save 2 cups of water that they are soaked in.
Pit and cut up the prunes.
Cook prunes, liquid, sugar, shortening, spices, and salt for 5 minutes.
Cool. Add eggs, flour, and soda.
Bake in 2 greased 5 x 9 inch loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick is clean when testing.

title: chinese chicken noodle salad
directions: Clean and chop cabbage.
Place in a large bowl.
Add green onions, chicken, Top Ramen noodles (broken up), sesame seed and slivered almonds.
Mix all together.
Add dressing.

title: grandma's lime salad
directions: Use fork to combine Jell-O mix and 2 cups of "boiling" water (this is important); add 2 cans of pear juice (from canned pears). Allow this to gel about halfway.
Use fork to whip the cream cheese (softened), mashed pears and Cool Whip in the half gelled Jell-O mixture.
Whip until thoroughly blended.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours until fully gelled.

title: cheddar-apple pie
directions: Arrange slices of apples in pastry shell.
Combine sugar, salt, and nutmeg; sprinkle over apples.
Dot with butter.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Preheat broiler.
To make marinade, combine garlic, oil, lemon juice, Worcestershire and pepper in bowl.
Cut chicken into 3/8-inch strips.
Marinate in sauce 10 to 20 minutes in refrigerator.
Slice onion and pepper into 1/8-inch strips.
In nonstick skillet, heat 2 teaspoons oil over medium heat.
Add onion and pepper and saute, stirring occasionally, until onion is brown.
Wrap tortillas in foil and heat in oven.
Line broiler pan with foil.
Place chicken on foil and broil about 3 inches from heat for 4 minutes.
Serve 3 chicken strips on each tortilla.
Top with onion, pepper and garnishes as desired.
Roll tortilla around chicken and eat with fingers.

title: clam cheese dip
directions: Mix all together.
Let sit for 1 hour.
Remove the garlic pieces.
Serve on crackers or with chips.

title: double chocolate fantasy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, beat cake mix, oil and egg on medium speed until crumbly.
Add nuts.
Reserving 1 1/2 cups of crumb mixture, press remainder firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a small saucepan, combine remaining ingredients and cook until chips melt.
Pour evenly over prepared crust.
Top with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or unti bubbly.
Cool.
Cut into 36 bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Roll out on well-floured surface to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into shapes. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Decorate with icing or granulated sugar.

title: depression cake
directions: Mix the sugar, coffee, shortening, raisins and apple.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes, then cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake hour at 350° in a 9-cup tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool 5 minutes before taking out of tube pan.

title: mock ravioli
directions: Put juices in pot.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add the basil.
Cook onions in butter.
Fry meat when done.
Drain off fat.
After onions and meat are fried, put in with the sauce. Simmer for about 40 minutes.
Cook bow ties and spinach.
Grate cheese.
Then put some meat sauce in bottom of casserole, then noodles, all spinach, cheese.
Repeat and finish with meat sauce. Put some of the cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Crumble sausage into large glass bowl.
Microwave, covered with plastic wrap, on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until no longer pink, turning bowl once.
Drain.
Add milk, eggs, dry mustard, salt, cheese and bread; mix well.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) round glass baking dishes.
Microwave 1 dish at a time on Defrost for 15 to 18 minutes, stirring and turning dish every 3 minutes. Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Spray one 9 x 13 x 2-inch quart baking dish with Pam.
Pour 1 quart of peaches in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle 1 box of dry cake mix over peaches.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix all together; chill and serve with nacho chips. Enjoy!!

title: meatless chili
directions: Heat oil.
Add chopped onions.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, picante sauce, chili powder, cumin and salt.
Cover. Cook on simmer 10 minutes.
Add beans, pepper, zucchini and corn. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until zucchini is tender.

title: olivia's ham-spinach quiche
directions: Prepare pie shell. Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Cool. Set oven to 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Bake 1 hour
at 325° in loaf pan.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Puree strawberries and milk in blender.
Add yogurt, sugar and vanilla; blend.
Chill 2 hours before serving.
This is a refreshing summer dish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Mix strawberries and glaze. Set aside.

title: baked beans
directions: Remove all pork from beans and discard.
Chop jalapenos with care; protect your skin.
Cook onion, peppers and jalapenos together in microwave about 3 minutes on High.
Mix beans and cooked vegetables with brown sugar and ketchup.
Mixture should have a dark red color.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add more sugar and/or ketchup to taste.
These beans keep well in fridge for several days.

title: pineapple sauce
directions: Combine both mustards, butter, olive oil, lemon rind, lemon juice and pepper in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until butter melts and mixture is hot, stirring occasionally.
Sauce can be made a day ahead and refrigerated, covered.
Gently reheat.

title: the best brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs; beat well with a spoon.
Combine flour and cocoa; gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from edges of pan.
Frost if desired; cut into squares.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Mix together sugar, salt, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, eggs, pumpkin, milk and water.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix well and bake as the box indicates for your size greased pan (8-inches).

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Crisply cook and crumble bacon.
Mix with other ingredients. Clean mushrooms; discard stems.
Fill mushroom caps; brush bottoms with oil.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 10 minutes and then broil for 3 minutes.

title: spaghetti - pizza style
directions: Cook spaghetti according to pkg. directions;
drain.
Toss spaghetti with 1 c. milk and eggs beaten together.
Place in greased 13 x 9 inch casserole dish.
Spread spaghetti sauce over top.
Top with pepperoni and shredded mozzarella.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: amalgamation filling
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar and butter.
Grind remaining ingredients together.
Add to first mixture and stir until well combined.
Use as filling for white or yellow cake.

title: oil and vinegar dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and shake well.
Let set 24 hours before serving.
No refrigeration needed.
(If you don't have an oil and vinegar shaker a sterilized pint size milk jug works well.)

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Broil about 10 minutes.
Makes 120.
Make Swedish Meatball Sauce and pour onto meatballs.

title: shelby's extra squirrelly fudge
directions: Mix butter, sugar and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan. Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly, to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in chips until melted.
Add creamy peanut butter. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 2 greased 8-inch square or one 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares. Makes 3 pounds.

title: low-fat spam casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with nonfat cooking spray.
Fry Spam in skillet.
Cut into bite-size pieces; drain fat.
(Rinse Spam with hot water to remove fat.)
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish; mix well.
Cook for 20 minutes; add cheese and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix and mold graham crackers, butter and sugar into pie dish and place in freezer until you mix pie.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, eggs and lemon juice and mix well.
Then add Cool Whip and mix. Pour in pie shell and place in refrigerator.
Sprinkle some graham cracker crumbs on top of pie.

title: lois hayes' dressing
directions: This recipe was given to me by my dear friend, Lois Hayes. Thanks to Mrs. Hayes for being such a good friend, leader and Christian Sister.
Mix and bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine all but vegetables. Heat until sugar is dissolved. Place vegetables in a 2 quart jar, pour liquid over them. Let cool enough to be placed in refrigerator. Ready to eat in 24 hours. These will keep up to one year in the refrigerator.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Flatten biscuits.
Place in muffin tins, pressing up the sides.
(Note:
Be sure biscuits are cold.
They tend to shrivel up if handled too long.)
Spoon meat mixture into cups and top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: seafoam icing
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Slowly add rest of ingredients. Beat with mixer in top of a double boiler over medium heat for about 10 minutes until it loses its gloss.

title: parmesan wonton crisps(this is a low-fat, lo-cal, tasty appetizer.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stack the wonton wrappers, then cut them in half diagonally to make 60 triangles.

title: tims peppers
directions: Slice jalapenos from stem to tip; open and scoop out seeds. Soak cleaned peppers in cold water. Brown ground beef with salt, pepper, garlic salt and chopped onions. Stuff peppers with ground beef mixture and press in grated Cheddar cheese. Wrap the whole pepper with 1 slice of bacon and secure with toothpick. Place peppers on grill and cook until bacon is done.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Break angel food cake into an oblong glass dish.
Cover bottom.
Combine milk, pudding and ice cream with electric mixer, pour over cake pieces.
Let set 1 hour in refrigerator.
Dissolve Jello in boiling water then add frozen strawberries.
Stir till thick, then pour over cake mixture and chill 1 hour.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown and drain hamburger; in frypan, add to hamburger, sauce, mushrooms and olives.
Grate cheese over mixture and cover to melt cheese.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Remove bones.
Put noodles in broth and bring to a boil.
Combine soups in a saucepan.
Heat and stir until well combined.
Add sour cream.

title: fruit pizza
directions: *Suggestions:
fresh pineapple, bananas sprinkled with Fruit-Fresh to prevent turning dark, kiwi, grapes, strawberries.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water, syrup and salt in saucepan until a drop in cold water forms a hard ball.
Pour over stiffly beaten egg whites in a thin stream.
Add vanilla and continue to beat until stiff. Fold in nuts.
Pour in pan lined with wax paper.
When set, cut in squares.

title: country chicken and biscuits
directions: Combine soup and milk in large bowl. Gently stir in chicken and green beans. Season with pepper. Spoon into 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Separate biscuit dough into individual biscuits. Arrange biscuits over hot cooked mixture and bake again for 15 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown and baked through. Makes 4 servings.

title: basic baked fish
directions: Wash fish thoroughly.
Place drained fish in single layer in foil-lined shallow baking pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over fish.
Bake at 350° until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork, 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: shrimp and scallop casserole
directions: Poach scallops 10 minutes in water to which you add 1 teaspoon lemon juice and 1 teaspoon salt.
Reserve 1/2 cup broth.

title: eloise's ozark sweet pickles
directions: Pack whole, small cucumbers in 1/2 gallon jar.
Add liquid and spices.
Seal.
Let set 3 weeks.
Drain liquid and throw away. Cut pickles at least once or slice.
Put back in jar.
Add 2 cups sugar.
Seal again.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Blend flour and sugar in a large bowl and set aside.
Mix together margarine, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil and pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Blend well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
While warm, frost.

title: poor man beef
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add soup and noodles.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat until hot.
Serve.

title: cajun barbecue shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Peel and devein shrimp.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Melt butter in a medium saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Whisk in remaining ingredients.
Arrange shrimp in a single layer in a 9 x 11-inch casserole, then pour butter mixture over shrimp.
Bake on center rack for 3 to 5 minutes.
Turn shrimp and bake for 2 minutes more.
Transfer shrimp to serving platter and pour on any remaining sauce.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together. Chill. Serve with fruit.

title: asparagus souffle
directions: Blend oil, 1/2 cup milk and parsley in double boiler.
Add 1 cup milk, stirring until mixture thickens.
Cool to lukewarm. Beat in egg yolks.
Add asparagus.
Turn into a greased casserole and bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat to a boil; boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Take off heat.
Stir in peanut butter chips until completely melted.
Stir in vanilla and optional nuts.
Spread in buttered pan.

title: chicken broth soup
directions: Boil chicken until tender in 8 cups water.
Remove chicken from boiler and cut into small pieces.
Add butter, celery soup, salt and pepper.
Mix together milk and flour and mix well to broth.
Stir until desired consistency.
Add chicken pieces and serve with crackers.

title: slush
directions: Mix all ingredients into noodles after noodles are drained. Heat on medium heat for about 15 minutes until warm throughout. Or bake in oven for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: bagels
directions: In bowl, combine flour and yeast.
In separate bowl, mix warm water, 3 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Pour over flour mix.
Beat on low for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl.
Beat 3 minutes on high.
Stir in as much remaining flour as you can with spoon.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Stir just to moisten.
Fill 12 greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: You will also need 8 wooden skewers

title: cheese pups
directions: Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Cut a slit down length of each frank and insert cheese.
Push skewers into one end of each frank.
Wrap franks in dough and pinch edges and ends to seal. Brush with sauce and dip in crumbs.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: honey candied popcorn
directions: Cook to hard ball stage.
Pour over packages of microwave popcorn or regular popped corn.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes until tender and mash well. Add butter, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Use a 9-inch pie crust, either homemade or frozen, and pour mixture into crust.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted in center of pie.

title: egg and cheese casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
In Osterizer or use hand mixer, mix eggs, milk, salt, pepper and mustard.
Pour over bread cubes.
Add drained sausage. Sprinkle cheese.
Use an 8 x 12-inch glass pan. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° until set. Test with knife. Can refrigerate overnight.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Mix butter, sugar and flour.
Spread in 11 x 15-inch pan. Beat eggs until light and add brown sugar.
Add flour and baking powder, which has been sifted together.
Mix well, until smooth and stir in pecans.
Spread over top of first mixture and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 60 squares.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in heavy saucepan; bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares.

title: czech crescent rolls
directions: Use a good brand of all-purpose flour.
Put lukewarm buttermilk or milk and water in a large Dutch oven.
Add yeast and sprinkle with sugar, about a tablespoon.
Let set for a while in a warm oven until very bubbly.

title: cinnamon applesauce ornaments
directions: Start with 1/4 cup applesauce and add more as needed.
Knead dough a few minutes.
If dough seems sticky, add more cinnamon. Roll out dough to approximately 1/4-inch.
Cut out with cookie cutters and punch hole at top to hang.
Lay on flat surface to dry.
When completely dry (may take a few days), string and hang.

title: ham and spinach turnovers
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare poached eggs, except cook 3 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.
Roll pastry in 18 x 10-inch rectangle on lightly floured surface.
Cut into 4 (10 x 4 1/2-inch) rectangles.
Layer drained and thawed spinach, ham, mustard, egg and cheese on one end of each rectangle to 1/2-inch of edge.
Fold pastry over cheese.
Fold edges of pastry, pinching firmly to seal.
Bake 15 minutes or until pastry is puffed and deep golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate-chip coffee cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and baking soda and beat again.
Spread 1/2 of batter in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and cover with 1/2 of sugar, cinnamon and chocolate chip mixture. Repeat.
(Layers will be thin.)
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until lightly golden.

title: lemon fruit pie
directions: Combine lemon juice and milk.
Stir in pecans and fruit cocktail.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell or some prefer vanilla wafer pie shell.
Slice bananas and put on top of pie mixture.
Chill.
Put on whipping cream or Cool Whip just before serving.
(You may prefer adding bananas just before serving, so they won't turn dark.)
This pie tastes like a banana split.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all together and bake 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells in salted water.
Drain and rinse.
Saute Italian sausage; drain.
If links, bake 1 hour at 350°, then cut into small pieces.
Stuff shells with sausage, Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish; cover with spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet crescents
directions: Lightly grease a cookie sheet.
Press rolls firmly onto sheet. Sprinkle with pecans.
Pour condensed milk evenly over the rolls. Bake at 350° for minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool before serving.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash and dry cucumbers.
Pack in jar in which you have already put dill, clove of garlic and pod of pepper, if desired.
Boil water, salt, vinegar and sugar.
Pour immediately over cucumbers and seal jar.
Hot water bath 5 to 10 minutes or until cucumbers turn slightly yellow.
Ready in 2 weeks.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken and let cool, then dice.
Mix all ingredients together, except almonds.
Use them for garnish.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Sprinkle rice over butter.
Place chicken over rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix.
Mix mushroom soup in water real good.
Then pour over chicken.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken and take off bones. Layer ingredients in casserole dish, starting with chicken, cooked rice, broccoli, cream of mushroom soup and cheese. Repeat all 5 again and use remaining cheese. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: ellen austin's pound cake
directions: Cream
sugar
and
shortening.	Beat well until smooth. Add eggs, one
at
a
time, beating after each egg.
Add flour and milk
alternately;	beat
just
enough
to	be mixed.
Add flavorings and mix	lightly.
Bake in a tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake	at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Check often toward the end of baking time.

title: sweet and sour shells
directions: Chop vegetables and drain juice off pimentos.
Mix soup, sugar, oil and vinegar until smooth.
Pour over shells and vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: syrup
directions: Cook for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; leave until cold.
The syrup must be ice cold when you drop the koeksisters into it. Roll out the dough until thin; cut into 1/4-inch strips and braid, then cut each braid into 3-inch pieces.
Fry in hot oil, three at a time.
Drop into ice cold syrup for a few minutes.
Take out, drain excess syrup and eat.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread; add onion, tomato, bell pepper, salt to taste, pepper to taste, salad dressing to taste and sweet relish to taste.
Mix well and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pizza meatballs
directions: Mix in bowl first 6 ingredients; shape mixture into medium sized meat balls with 1 cube of cheese in center of each, making sure that cheese is completely covered with meat mixture.
Coat each meatball lightly with flour.
In skillet, over medium high heat, in hot oil, cook meatballs until browned on all sides. Put meatballs in sauce and simmer until heated.
Serve on rice or spaghetti.

title: speedy italian supper
directions: Cook bacon crisp; drain and crumble.
Saute celery and onions in 1 tablespoon of drippings.
Add mushrooms and spaghetti.
Heat to bubbling; sprinkle with bacon.

title: bisquick zucchini
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes or until brown.

title: chex mix
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chips; remove from heat. Add vanilla.
Pour over chips.
Coat well.
Add powdered sugar in a paper bag or plastic bowl with lid.
Shake until cereal is well coated.

title: swedish bars
directions: Cook raisins in water for 10 minutes; cool.
Cream sugar and margarine well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add vanilla and cooked raisins, mixing well.
Add sifted flour and baking soda; mix.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, make glaze of confectioners sugar and a little water.
Spread on top.
Cut in squares.

title: italian stew
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat in oil; add onions and garlic.
Stir in paste, flour, chili powder, oregano, rosemary, seasoned salt, tomatoes and parsley.
Add 1 cup water. Simmer covered 1 hour. Add carrots; simmer 45 minutes.
Cook pasta; drain and stir into stew with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fig cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add oil and beat well.
Add eggs and buttermilk gradually.
Add figs, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: michelle's marvelous mountain bars
directions: Mix together butter, sugar and milk in a double boiler and let boil for 1 minute.
Add last three ingredients; mix well. Drop mixture by spoonfuls onto waxed paper placed on a cookie sheet or tray; chill at least 1/2 hour.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave Method:
In large glass bowl, combine chocolate chips and milk.
Microwave on High 3 minutes.
Stir until melted and mixture is smooth.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm (about 2 hours).
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds fudge.

title: cinnamon crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in honey, vanilla and eggs, then blend with first mixture, flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and oats.
Drop dough onto greased cookie sheet with scoop.
Press flat.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: garlicky broiled chicken
directions: In a shallow bowl, stir together lemon juice, oil, wine, garlic and bay leaves.
Rinse and drain chicken; add to marinade and turn to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or up to 1 day, turning chicken occasionally.

title: vegetable soup and everything but coal-oil soup
directions: In very large pot, cook meat and onions until meat is brown. Add remaining ingredients, except for margarine.
Can be eaten when carrots and potatoes are tender, but better when simmered 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.
Add margarine about 30 minutes before serving.
Remove bay leaves. Freezes well.
Serve with corn bread.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: Sprinkle steak with paprika.
Let stand while preparing other ingredients.
Cook steak in butter and garlic salt until browned. Add onion and green pepper.
Add tomatoes and broth; cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: cajun rice and chicken
directions: Cut up cooked chicken into 1/2-inch strips.
Combine with cooked rice and beans.
Mix well.
Can be served hot or cold.
For cold salad, chill all ingredients.

title: cheddar cheese pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Heat oven to 325°.
Heat cheese, onion, salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce over low heat, stirring until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add cheese mixture and continue beating until smooth.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Bake 25 minutes or until filling is just set.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet. Add onion, celery and garlic.
Drain. Add remaining ingredients except macaroni. Stir to blend and break apart tomatoes. Cover and simmer until celery is tender.
Stir in macaroni. Re-cover and simmer until heated.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in oleo until light brown, about 20 minutes.
Add broth and Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.

title: red ruby
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water; let cool.
Stir in juices.
Just before serving, stir in club soda and, if desired, vodka.
Serve over ice.
Yields about 7 cups.

title: lemon potatoes(micro magic)
directions: On High, microwave butter in 8-inch round baking dish for 30 to 45 seconds until melted.
Mix lemon juice, salt and potato slices and coat evenly.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes, or until tender.
Stir once.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley and serve immediately.

title: dill pickle syrup
directions: Drain and slice pickles.
Combine sugar, water and vinegar in saucepan.
Boil until clear.
Pour syrup over pickles.
Cool. After cooled, refrigerate.

title: wild rice with mushrooms
directions: Steam rice or cook according to directions on package.
Saute mushrooms and green onions in the oil. Stir in margarine and rice. Serve hot.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until tender.
Peel and dice.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch casserole. Heat cream cheese until melted. Stir in sour cream.
Add milk if needed to make mixture pourable. Salt and pepper potatoes to taste.
Add chopped chives.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: gabby's mustard and sausage
directions: Mix in a small bowl with wire whisk.
Pour into two (1/2 pint) jars or tiny jars that you've saved.
Refrigerate for 7 days. Stir before serving with elk or deer sausage or ham and cheese slices or cocktail smokies.

title: honey glazed chicken wings
directions: Mix soy sauce, lemon juice and honey to use as a glaze.
Cover chicken with some of the glaze before cooking and let marinade for at least 1/2 hour.
Remove from marinade and cook either in the oven or on the grill.
Continue to baste during cooking with remaining glaze.

title: iris marsh's fruit salad
directions: Heat and stir the jello, 1 cup juice and 1 cup marshmallows until the marshmallows melt.
Cool and add Cool Whip, cottage cheese, drained fruit cocktail, mandarin oranges and nuts.
Mix and chill until firm in a large baking dish.

title: pecan pie
directions: Chill crust.
Heat oven to 325°.
Beat oleo until creamy.
Add sugar slowly and beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in syrups. Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake 1 hour.

title: christmas nutcake
directions: Separate eggs; beat until foamy, but not stiff.
Chop nuts. Place all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: beef fajita salad
directions: Trim fat from meat.
Place in a Ziploc bag; add the lime juice and next 3 ingredients and seal.
Marinate 6 to 8 hours.

title: shrimp aloha
directions: Boil shrimp, shell and devein.
Mix remaining ingredients and heat.
Add cooked shrimp.
Do not boil.
Serve over fluffy white rice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients; add remainder. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased Bundt pan. Cool 20 minutes and put on cake rack.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Bake at 350° until done.

title: yummy jello
directions: Bring 3 cups water to a boil.
Add jello and pudding.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes or until dissolved.
Let cool and stir in Cool Whip and oranges.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and let stand in ice (in refrigerator) overnight.
Add to each jar 1 clove garlic, sprig of dill, 1 grape leaf and 1 hot red pepper (optional).
Sterilize jars and lids. Add cucumbers.
Boil 3 quarts of water, 1 quart cider vinegar and 1 cup coarse medium salt.
Pour over cucumbers and seal.
To seal, boil in open pot, cover jars with water for 10 minutes.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cook grits in water.
Add cheese, milk, eggs, margarine, salt and pepper.
Pour into a buttered 4-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: dried beef appetizer balls
directions: Chop dried beef very fine and mix 1/3 of it with remaining ingredients.
Chill mixture for approximately an hour.
Form cheese-beef mixture into 1/2-inch balls and roll in remaining dried beef.
Spear with wooden picks.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in tightly covered container. Put 3 heaping teaspoonfuls to a cup.
Add hot water and stir.

title: banana icebox cake
directions: Line a layer of vanilla wafers on a flat cake plate.
Spread on whipped cream and sliced bananas; repeat until all ingredients have been used.
You may trim the top with cherries or with colored candy drops. Chill until firm.

title: peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips.
Put them in last.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: red fruit jelly with cream(rodgrod med flode)
directions: Wash the berries (there is no need to remove the stalks). Place in layers in an enamel saucepan, adding just enough water to cover.
Bring slowly to the boil and simmer until the fruit has all broken up and the juice is dark red in color.

title: honey tomato fish fillets
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion in oil until golden.
Stir in garlic.
Add remaining ingredients except fish and cook over medium heat, about 10 minutes.

title: meat-cheese roll
directions: Combine beef, egg, bread crumbs, onions, 1/3 cup tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well and shape into a flat rectangle about 10 x 12-inches on a piece of wax paper.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups cheese evenly over meat mixture.
Starting with shortest end, roll up jelly roll fashion and press ends of roll to seal.
Bake in a shallow baking pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Drain of excess fat.
Pour remaining sauce over roll.
Garnish with remaining 1/2 cup cheese. Bake additional 5 minutes or until cheese starts to melt.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift in flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Add raisins.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan (greased) and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve plain with powdered sugar or with chocolate frosting.

title: coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until set which is about 30 minutes or so.
Dust with nutmeg, if desired.

title: spicy pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add salad oil, sugar and vanilla.
Continue to beat until thick and foamy.
Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, walnuts and raisins.
Stir gently until well mixed.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all together.
Mix with any kind of cooked, chopped meat.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salt water until tender.
Drain.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Make sauce of rest of the ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: biscuit pull apart bread
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in small saucepan.
Cook until mixture boils.
Set aside.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk, butter and vanilla to boil. Boil for 1 minute and remove from fire. Add peanut butter, raw oats and nuts (if desired). Stir well and drop from spoon onto cookie sheet. Let set for 30 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: In a stockpot, brown beef and drain well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix granulated sugar, brown sugar, margarine or butter, peanut butter, vanilla and eggs together well.
Add the dry ingredients. Add the chocolate chips.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
For a crunchy cookie, cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute.

title: steak and zucchini dinner
directions: In skillet, quickly brown steak in hot oil.
Add gravy, water and spaghetti sauce mix; stir until well combined.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add zucchini.
Cover and continue cooking for 10 to 12 minutes, until zucchini is tender-crisp. Serve over noodles or rice, if desired.

title: oreo pie
directions: Let Cool Whip and ice cream sit out for 20 to 30 minutes. Crust cookies in a Ziploc bag.
Mix Cool Whip, ice cream and cookies together.
Pour into pie crusts and freeze.
For appearance, take whole Oreos and stick in tops of the pies.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Drain off excess grease. Add all together.
For chili mac, add medium pack of cooked noodles.
Let simmer for 1 to 2 hours.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Cut crab meat in chunks.
Combine dressings and cheese.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Chill.
Serve with freshly ground black pepper (if desired).

title: mashed potatoes au gratin
directions: Cook the potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain and dry over heat in the pan.
Put through a potato ricer in a bowl.
Add the butter, salt and pepper; blend well.
Gradually blend in cream until you have the desired consistency.
The mixture should not be too thin.
Spoon the potatoes into a shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle evenly with a mixture of cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake in a preheated 400 degree oven until heated through and golden on top.
Or, if the potatoes are very hot, place under broiler until golden on top.

title: spring garden
directions: Brown the beef and onions.
Pour off fat.
Add carrots, beans, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken patties
directions: Cook hen til tender...whack up into pieces but hold on to the broth (never throw broth away...put eny thet's left over in the freezer 'r in the ice box.)
Brown onion in buttah 'n stir in the flour, salt 'n pepper...pore in the milk 'n cook til kinda bubley like...then take off the stove.
Now mix this wid the chicken in a shallow bowl...kiver wid sumph 'n put in the ice box all nite.

title: italian spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti. Cool in cold water for 5 minutes; drain.
Add chopped vegetables, salad dressing and seasoning.
Mix and chill several hours.
May add more onions, if desired.

title: mom's rice pudding
directions: Combine rice and water and cook until rice is cooked.
Add the eggs, sugar and milk and cook until all blended and thickened. Can add raisins and vanilla. Stir.
Pour into bowl; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
When cool, serve topped with whipped cream.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Combine peppers, jalapeno peppers, sugar and vinegar.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 1 minute, stirring to prevent boiling over.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pectin.
Mix well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Skim off white film on top.
Mix in food coloring.
Strain if you prefer a clear jelly.
Pour into hot sterilized jars.
Top with sterilized 2 part jar lids and tighten bands.
Cool on rack. Makes 6 ounce jars.

title: scampi
directions: Prepare shrimp and refrigerate.

title: bruschetla rossa
directions: Place the tomatoes in a large bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Set aside 6 large basil leaves.
Stack the remaining basil leaves.
Slice them thin.
Sprinkle over the tomatoes.
Add all but 2 pieces of the halved garlic and the olive oil.
Stir to combine.
Leave at room temperature for 1 to 2 hours.

title: cornbread
directions: Stir cheese, corn and onions into cornbread mixture. Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Drain pineapple into saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; add jello and pineapple.
Do not add water to jello.
When this cools, add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Melt marshmallows and jello in boiling water.
Cool slightly. Add cream cheese; stir until blended.
Add pineapple juice.
Chill until mixture starts to thicken.
Add crushed pineapple and nuts.

title: almond butter crunch wheels
directions: Line bottom and sides of 8 or 9-inch cake pan with foil. Butter foil heavily.
Combine almonds, butter, brown sugar and corn syrup in 10-inch skillet.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil, stirring constantly, until mixture turns golden brown, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Working quickly, spread candy in prepared pan.
Cool about 15 minutes or until firm. Remove candy from pan by lifting edges of foil.
Peel off foil. Cool thoroughly.
Candy may be given as gift in 1 piece or broken into pieces.
Makes about 3/4 pound.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar, brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil 2 minutes (no more).
Take off stove immediately.
Add peanut butter and Marshmallow Fluff.
Beat until mixed and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 3 pounds.
Cool before cutting into pieces.
Serves 40.

title: butter cookies(diabetic)
directions: Cream butter and sweetener.
Sift in dry ingredients and add vanilla.
Form into roll; wrap in foil or wax paper.
Chill for 6 to 8 hours.
Slice thin.
Bake 15 minutes in preheated 375° oven.

title: marie's pink stuff
directions: Mix together thoroughly!
May add pecans or coconut if desired.

title: mayo cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda and cocoa.
Beat water and mayo together.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Heat the last five items in pan.
Place chicken in greased pan.
Place doritoes on top.
Pour sauce over all and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: antipasta
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for at least 12 to 24 hours before serving.
Ingredients and quantities can be varied, depending on your own preferences.

title: preacher's casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions and celery and cook until vegetables are clear.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole; top with 1/4 cup noodles, crushed, and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot chicken souffle
directions: Put 2 slices of bread or cubes on bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine chicken or turkey, if preferred, vegetables, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Spread over bread.
Trim 4 slices of bread.
Put over chicken mixture.
Combine eggs and milk.
Pour over mixture.
Chill 1 hour or overnight.
(The longer it sets, the better.)
Spoon soup over top.
Sprinkle cheese over the last minute.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Serve with peas, rolls, cole slaw, fruit cocktail and cookies.
Serves 6.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook over medium heat until done.
Put everything together, bacon on top, and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Beat well and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: firehall punch
directions: Mix all together and chill. Serve over ice.

title: oatmeal tea cakes
directions: Mix lard, sugar and egg.
Add milk with flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and oats.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Grease (or use paper liners) small muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hungarian coffee cake
directions: Pour into two greased and floured cake pans (line bottom with wax paper) and crumble other half on top.
Dot with more butter and cinnamon.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: mushroom appetizers
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
(Leave mushrooms whole.) Place on a cookie sheet, button side up; fill each mushroom with dry soup mix (approximately 1/2 teaspoon).
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 2 minutes until butter has melted.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Brown ground meat.
When meat is half cooked, put in onion, celery and bell peppers; cook until done.
Add cooked rice and stir well, then add 1/3 can tomato sauce, then stir in Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Have bell peppers set aside already boiled, with pinch of salt.
Stuff peppers; pour extra tomato sauce lightly over bell peppers.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° on a preheated cookie sheet for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook cut up chicken in butter until done, DO NOT DRAIN.
Add peas, carrots, soup and milk.
Cook until soup is done; add salt and pepper.
Mix Bisquick using directions on box.
Add parsley to Bisquick; add heaping spoons of Bisquick to chicken mix.
Cover pan for 35 minutes or until dumplings are done.
DO NOT STIR PAN!!

title: sausage cheese dip
directions: Spray crock-pot with Pam spray. Fry sausage and drain.
Put crock-pot on high.
Add milk, cheese cubes, cooked sausage and pimentos.
When cheese has melted, turn to low.
Serve with chips.
Also great over hot biscuits.

title: fresh corn
directions: Fry bacon in skillet, then remove.
Add water, salt and sugar to
bacon
drippings and bring to a boil.
Add corn and cabbage and
cook,
covered,
until
tender, about 7 minutes, stirring frequently.
Garnish with bacon strips.

title: banana pudding supreme
directions: Mix cream cheese until softened and mix in Eagle Brand milk. Mix vanilla pudding and 2 cups milk in a separate bowl until thick.
Add to cheese and Eagle Brand mixture.
Fold in 1/2 carton of Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers and sliced bananas and spread mixture over layers.
Top off with remainder of Cool Whip.

title: torpedo
directions: Boil all ingredients together, except tomato paste and tomato sauce, for 20 minutes.
Add the tomato sauce and tomato paste; let simmer for 2 hours.
Serve over buns.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and shape into balls (small).
Mix remaining ingredients and melt over medium heat.
Put raw meatballs into hot sauce.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Refrigerate and reheat before serving.
Tastes best when made a day ahead and reheated. Makes approximately 72.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Rub flour into roast; brush off excess.
Heat oil and 2 tablespoons of the butter in a 5-quart kettle over medium-high heat.
Add meat and brown well on all sides.
Add bay leaf, pepper, thyme, beef broth and water; bring to a boil.
Cover and place in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburger soup
directions: *Five cans of beef broth can be substituted for water and eliminate salt.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and shake well.
Refrigerate.
Yield: 3 1/4 cups.

title: diet breakfast drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend on high speed until mixed.

title: graham-marshmallow squares
directions: Mix eggs, butter and sugar in a microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High for about 4 minutes, stirring once at 2 minutes. Mix the remaining ingredients with the egg mixture.
Pour into buttered 8-inch pan.
Cool.

title: suet pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients and mix with the moist batter.
Steam pudding 3 1/2 hours.
Make sure you ask for suet when making this so they don't give you tallow.
There is a difference.

title: china sun pork
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 3 tablespoons of juice.
Mix reserved juice with 1/2 cup water, soy sauce, cornstarch, vinegar and pepper flakes.
Set aside.
Cut pork in strips.
In skillet or wok, brown pork in hot oil.
Add garlic and ginger.
Cook 1 minute. Add onion and carrots.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir sauce.
Add to pork with pineapple and bell pepper.
Cook until sauce boils or thickens.
Serves 4. Good by itself or over cooked rice.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cornmeal.
Add lightly beaten eggs. Add butter and blend thoroughly.
Add milk, grated lemon rind and juice.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Melt butter and cheese over hot water; using a double boiler. Cut bread into 1-inch square cubes.
When cheese is melted; stir to combine and fold in beaten egg whites.
Dip bread cubes into cheese mixture.
Place on tray covered with waxed paper.
Place in freezer.
When frozen, put in plastic bag to store.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Sprinkle flour over cake mix and mix well. Add jello, oil, water and strawberries. Mix with electric mixer. Add egg whites, one at a time, and mix well. Pour into a greased Bundt pan. Bake for about 45 minutes at 350°. After cooling slightly, can be dusted with powdered sugar or a glaze.

title: prosciutto with melon
directions: Melon should be ripe and chilled.
Cut in half and remove seeds.
Slice into pieces 3/4-inch wide.
Cut along bottom of flesh near rind, but do not separate rind from melon.
This makes the melon easier to eat and preserves its appearance.
Put 2 slices of Prosciutto on each melon slice.
Serve 2 melon slices per person.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches evenly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut larger peaches and spread around.
Pour cake mix over the peaches, then pour melted margarine over the cake mix.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: can't resist rum cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Sprinkle chopped pecans on bottom of pan.
Pour cake mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
With cake still in pan, poke holes in cake with a skewer.
Glaze while in pan.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: Fry vegetables in oil until tender-crisp.
Sprinkle with sugar and salt.
Pour mushrooms over all ingredients with liquid.
Stir and fry 10 minutes.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In mixing bowl, blend the Crisco and granulated sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine the cake flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk, vanilla and lemon extract to shortening-sugar mixture.
Beat until mixture is smooth.
Turn batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until cake tests done.
Cool 1 hour; remove cake from pan and cool completely on rack.
To serve, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: mexican pile-on
directions: Crush
chips into small pieces.
Cook rice according to package directions.
To
serve, layer on a dinner plate in the order ingredients are
listed
using
2/3 cup of chips and 2/3 cup chili
per person.	Remaining ingredients are used according to taste.
May
be served in flour tortilla shell.
Serves 6.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Beat well, about 1 minute.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into greased and floured angel food pan.
(Can also use 2 bread pans.)
Bake.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Spoon about 5 tablespoons of glaze over cake.
Invert onto plate.
Spoon on remaining glaze.

title: creamy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water (12 to 15 minutes).
Drain well. Add next 5 ingredients.
Melt 3/4 stick margarine in pan, add stuffing and mix well.
Put in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish. Reserve some of stuffing for topping.
Pour squash mixture over stuffing and sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Dot remainder of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk all at once and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Arrange half of cooked broccoli and all of the eggs, sliced, in bottom of baking dish.
Add half the sauce and rest of broccoli.
Toss cracker crumbs with remaining butter and spread on top.

title: candied orange rind
directions: Read directions all the way through before starting.

title: easy dessert surprise
directions: Place a kiss in the center of biscuit; wrap and seal.
Place in sprayed casserole dish.
Scatter a few more kisses on top.
Top with frosting.
Bake at 375° until biscuits are done.

title: refrigerator pie
directions: Crush crackers; roll very fine.
Line glass pie plate with half of cracker crumbs, but do not butter plate.
Cream butter; slowly add sugar.
Mix well.
Add unbeaten egg; whip thoroughly. Smooth mixture over plate with crumbs.
Whip cream, fold in pineapple and cover pie.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Cool 6 hours before serving.

title: oreo delight
directions: Mix together and press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Save 3/4 cup of cookies for topping.

title: mrs. west icebox cookies
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco, eggs and vanilla.
Then add the flour. (Mix soda and cream of tartar with 2 cups flour and roll the dates and nuts in 1 cup of flour).
Make a stiff dough.
Form into a roll and put on wax paper.
Refrigerate 12 hours or you may drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not brown or they will be hard!
If you like soft cookie, put a slice of bread into the cookie container.
Makes 4 dozen small cookies.

title: jerri jo's favorite quiche
directions: Prepare pastry shell as usual. Combine milk, mayonnaise and flour until smooth. Add remaining ingredients and mix. Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tart salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except fruit cocktail with electric mixer. Fold cocktail in until smooth.
Place in freezer overnight. Serve when desired.

title: cider-baked turkey breast
directions: Preheat
oven
Place turkey breast, skin side up, in a large roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes. Remove turkey from oven and lower oven to 325°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Whip vanilla pudding with 3 cups milk.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream.
Add vanilla.
Line pan with wafers, bananas and pudding in layers until pan is full.

title: luau coleslaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Chill. Just before serving, add cabbage and orange sections and toss until evenly coated.
Add cubed cranberry sauce.
Toss lightly. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cabbage & kielbasa dish
directions: Cook cabbage and sauerkraut together.
Slice the kielbasa and fry with onion.
Mix
cabbage and kielbasa together.
Enjoy.

title: country bean soup
directions: Soak the beans overnight just covering beans with water and 3 teaspoons salt.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer 4 hours or longer, stirring often.

title: ora's lemon chess pie
directions: Cream soft butter, sugar and cornmeal.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add juice and rind.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300°, until firm and slightly brown.
Test with point of knife.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add taco seasoning and taco sauce.
Place pieces of taco shells in bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Add 1 layer of meat mixture.
Sprinkle with taco or sharp cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave 3 to 5 minutes or until hot.
Remove and cover with sour cream, onion, tomato, lettuce and cheese.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Brown chicken in skillet; add onion and cook about 5 minutes. Add tomato, raisins and enough water (about 1/4 cup) to allow for simmering until chicken is tender.
Add olives last.

title: italian salad
directions: Wash, dry, and tear romaine lettuce into bite size pieces. Add artichokes, pimentos, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Toss well with dressing.
Let sit 10 minutes before serving.

title: french lettuce peas
directions: Cook peas in boiling, salted water until almost tender.
Drain water.
Stir in onion, lettuce, butter and sugar.
Cover and cook over high heat a few minutes until onions and lettuce are limp. Salt to taste.
Add almonds, if desired.
Bake 5 minutes at 400°.

title: turkish meatball dinner (kofte)(pronounced kerftay)
directions: Mix everything but egg evenly into meat.
Add 1 egg and mix all together.
Make into oval balls.
Cover bottom of skillet in water, cook each meatball in the water, turning continually.
Do not brown.

title: glenn's favorite
directions: In microwave, warm 2 burritos to desired heat.
Place 1 tortilla on griddle, place 1/2 of cheese on half tortilla and fold over.
Repeat for second tortilla.
Cook over medium heat.
If you have a good griddle, no Pam or oil is needed and tortillas will be more crispy.
Top burritos with picante sauce and no-fat sour cream to taste.
Dip quesadilla in ketchup (lots of it)!

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Have all ingredients ready because it sets fast!
Dissolve orange Jell-O in the 1 cup of boiling water.
Fold in orange sherbet until dissolved.
Fold in fruit and Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or any container to be used as a mold.
Happy eating!

title: squash casserole
directions: Fry bacon; set aside. Cook squash and onion until tender. Drain off most of the water. Add cracker crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper. Add crumbled up bacon; mix well. Place in baking dish. Pour 2 tablespoons of bacon grease over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tarragon vinaigrette
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender cup.
Process until smooth.
Yield: 1/2 cup.

title: pasta and vegetables
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package; drain.
Cook and stir zucchini, tomato, onion, pepper and garlic in oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Stir in pasta and the remaining ingredients.
Cook about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is crisp-tender.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Any other combination of vegetables may be added.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups (or use paper liners).

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put butter in baking dish and place in 250° oven to melt; add peaches. In a separate bowl, mix the sugar and flour; add milk. Pour over the butter and peach mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.

title: double pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter and pour into 2 cake pans evenly.
Brush butter on all sides.
Take 2/3 cup brown sugar (half) and mix with butter. Spread evenly on bottom of pan.
Arrange "half" pineapple slices (10) on each pan, making a pinwheel pattern.
If you like, add cherries to center and in between each 1/2 slice of pineapple. Mix cake according to box and pour 1/2 batter into each pan.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serve separately or make a 2 layer cake.

title: green bean-corn casserole
directions: Grease a casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza ii
directions: Roll out crescent rolls on a 13 x 9-inch cookie sheet, covering the bottom with the crescent dough. Bake dough at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: hot seafood spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in remaining ingredients except almonds and paprika.
Spread mixture in 9-inch pie plate.
Top with almonds and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve with assorted crackers or vegetables.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat together first 5 ingredients, then mix in 1 cup milk. Pour over rhubarb (1/2-inch of rhubarb in pie pan) in pie crust. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; shred coarsely.
In saucepan on low heat, combine cheese and butter and stir until almost melted.
Remove and add sour cream, chives, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes. Turn into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: party cheese wreath
directions: Beat cream cheese and Cheddar cheese in bowl with electric mixer on medium until well blended.
Add bell pepper, onion and Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Put glass in center of serving tray and drop by spoon around glass.
Remove glass and serve.

title: berry-dijon pork chops
directions: Mix preserves, mustard and black pepper in a bowl; set aside. Heat olive oil, in a large skillet, over medium-high heat.
Add pork chops and brown 3 minutes on each side.
Spoon preserves mixture on top of pork chops, cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.

title: tuesdee salad
directions: Add equal parts olive oil and lemon juice to a large bowl. Add 1 small can sliced olives, 2 cloves crushed garlic, salt and pepper to taste and a dash of mustard powder.
Mix, then add greens.
Then cover with Parmesan cheese and toss again.
Serves 3 to 6.

title: spinach dorinne
directions: Cook spinach according to directions.
Drain and reserve liquor.
Melt butter in pan over low heat.
Add onion; cook until soft, but not brown.
Add flour, stirring until smooth, but not brown.
Add liquor.
Stir until smooth. Add milk and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Add seasonings and cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Combine with cooked spinach.
Put in casserole, top with bread crumbs and bake just until heated through at 350°.
(This may be served without baking.)

title: easy strawberry yogurt mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
When cool, add yogurt, mixing well.
Add strawberries and bananas.
Put into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: stuffed ham cruse style
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ham into a paste (if thinning is necessary, use sweed pickle juice or bourbon).
Put the yolks of the eggs and the whites of 2 through grinder before mixing into the paste.
Slit ham lengthwise, a deep gash down the center, then slice on either side of center gash.
Force the stuffing into the openings and pack tightly.
Cover the top and sides with the remaining stuffing.
Pat on smoothly.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, onion, green peppers, red peppers and salt in a large cooker or canner.
Mix well and let stand overnight. Drain and rinse well with cold water.
Add remaining ingredients and boil 20 to 30 minutes.
Ladle into hot jars and adjust lids. Process in boiling water bath 15 minutes. Makes 6 pints.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken on bottom of dish.
Put 1 slice of cheese over each piece of chicken.
Mix soup and milk over low heat; spread over cheese.
Sprinkle dressing over soup, then margarine.
Cook in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
If it starts browning too much, cover with foil.
A good company dish.

title: praline french toast
directions: Blend eggs, half and half, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and vanilla.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in pan.
Place in one layer of bread; pour in remaining liquid.
Refrigerate overnight.
In another 9 x 13-inch pan, melt oleo, brown sugar, syrup and nuts. Place the soaked bread on top of the mixture.
Bake at 350° until puffed and brown, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush cookies; set aside 1/3 cup for top.
Melt butter and mix with remaining cookies.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze for 10 minutes.
Mix pudding with milk and ice cream.
Pour over cookies. Let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Put Cool Whip on top of pudding mixture and sprinkle with 1/3 cup cookies.
Serve and refrigerate any leftover.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add mashed bananas, then add flour and soda, sifted together.
Add nuts last.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: banana nut bread #1
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and bananas.
Add eggs and jam.
Beat well.
Stir soda and flour.
Add to mixture.
Add nuts. Pour into well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain well.
Stir in next 4 ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles according to package but use 1/4 teaspoon garlic salt and 1 teaspoon vegetable oil.
Drain.
Layer half of the noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and meat sauce in a 9 x 13-inch pan which has been sprayed with Pam.
Then repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes and serve.

title: blackberry jam cake (layer)
directions: Cream butter and sugar gradually until light and fluffy.
Add unbeaten egg yolks, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add allspice, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Mix thoroughly.
Add sour cream or buttermilk into which soda has been added.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in layer pans.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini.
Boil about 5 minutes; drain.
Mix all other ingredients with zucchini.
Put into greased casserole.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 325°, about 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: banana cake
directions: Bake cake in 3 layers.
Cook icing in saucepan medium to high. When it bubbles up, remove from heat.
Put between layers of cakes, punching holes in cake so icing will go in.
Put sliced bananas between layers also.
Stack while hot.

title: busy day peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a square pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Pour over butter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mile-hi strawberry pie
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
(except whipping cream) in a large bowl
and
beat
at medium speed 15 minutes until stiff. Whip
the cream
until
stiff.
Fold into strawberry mixture. Pile into a pie pan and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Top with black olives and pepperoni.
Bake in shallow dish or pie pan at 325° for 25 minutes. Serve with Ry-Krisp, Triscuits or vegies.

title: fruit and yogurt breakfast
directions: In small mixer bowl, stir together yogurt, granola, banana and pear.
Spoon into 2 bowls.
Sprinkle with granola.
Yields 2 servings.

title: mini chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Heat the oven to 300°.
Paper line 30 muffin cups.
Stir together crumbs, sugar, cocoa and butter.
Press equal portions on bottom of prepared cups.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon batter into cups.
Top with mini chips.
Bake 20 minutes. Cool.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Beat together well and bake in 3 (8-inch) layers for 20 minutes or 2 (9-inch) layers for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: cheese, peas, potatoes
directions: Melt cheese completely.
Stir in peas, potatoes and pepperoni. Place in foil.
Grill foil packet 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip muffins
directions: Grease muffin cups or use paper baking cups.
Thoroughly mix flour, sugar, pie spice, baking soda, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Break eggs into another bowl.
Add pumpkin and butter and whisk until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour over dry ingredients and fold in with a rubber spatula just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Scoop batter evenly into muffin cups. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until puffed and springy to the touch in the center.
Turn out onto a rack to cool.
Wrap in a plastic bag and keep for 1 or
2 days.
Makes 12 regular or 48 miniature muffins.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Tear cake into small pieces.
Place half cake pieces in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In top of double boiler over hot water, melt chocolate pieces.
Cool.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon color.
Stir in chocolate.

title: hot beef
directions: Combine all and put in crock pot on low for 16 - 24 hours. About 2 hours before meat is ready, shred (stirring it with a spoon will make the meat fall apart) and continue to cook.
Add juice from 1 qt. dill pickles. 1/2 jar dill pickles diced fine.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown chops in oil. Remove chops from pan.
Pour off fat.
In same skillet, combine lemon juice and cornstarch; mix well.
Add sugar, onion, soy sauce, bouillon and reserved pineapple juice; cook and stir until slightly thickened and bouillon is dissolved.
Add pork chops and carrots. Cover and bake 45 minutes or until tender.
Add pineapple, cover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.
Garnish with green pepper, if desired.

title: italian chicken
directions: Dip pieces of chicken in dressing and bake in oven dish for 1 hour at 375°.

title: pimiento cheese
directions: Soften Velveeta.
Add sugar and mayonnaise.
Stir to mix.
May need to add more mayonnaise for right consistency.
Add pimientos and mix.
Serve with snack crackers or on bread as a sandwich.

title: chocolate custard ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in heavy pan.
Add chocolate and milk.
Cook until thickened or coats a spoon.
Add small amount of hot mixture to eggs.
Add to rest of mixture and cook for 1 minute longer.
Add vanilla.
Pour in ice cream freezer can.
Chill.
Add cream and freeze as usual.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into large casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cover top with 1 sleeve of Ritz or Town House crackers that have been crushed.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and pour over cracker crumbs. Continue baking 15 minutes longer.

title: fresh strawberries with sour cream
directions: Wash the berries by placing them briefly in a large bowl of cold water.
Pick them out quickly, one at a time, and as you do, remove the stems and hulls.
Place the berries on paper towels to drain; let them stand until they are thoroughly dry.

title: baked lima beans in chili sauce
directions: Soak the beans overnight in enough water to completely cover. Drain. Add enough fresh water to cover and bring to a boil. Add the salt and sugar.
Cook over low heat 1 1/2 hours.
Drain. Combine the beans, chili sauce, fat and bay leaf in a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: crumb topped vidalia onion rings(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, melt butter on High for 45 seconds or 1 minute.
Add onions and toss to coat.
Cover and cook on High for 4 to 6 minutes (microwave), stirring once.
Combine crumbs, cheese and paprika.
Spoon onto onions, cover with paper towel and microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy divinity
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook until it reaches a hard ball stage.
Add gelatin to beaten egg whites.
Pour syrup mixture in thin stream.
Beat until gloss is gone.
Stir in nuts and coconut.

title: rock shrimp and oyster manquechou
directions: Fry the bacon until crisp in a heavy 4-quart casserole; drain the fat.
Add the onion, garlic and green pepper; cook until onion is translucent, but not brown.
Stir in the corn and tomatoes. Add the tomato liquid, oyster liquid and cayenne pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes or until the corn is tender.
Add the shrimp and oysters and cook for 2 minutes or until the edges of the oysters begin to curl.
Serve at once.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Make pudding according to recipe on box.
Mix pudding and Cool Whip in a bowl.
Spoon into pie crust.
Top with jimmies.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: meat sauce for hot dogs
directions: Mix together then cook very slow for two to three hours. Don't cook meat first.
Can be put into containers and put into the freezer for later use.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease loaf pan, 13 x 9-inch.
Drain pineapple.
Spread in pan. Spread peach pie filling over pineapple.
Pour cake mix over pie filling.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix; place sliced pats of butter over top.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well mixed.	Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour into 2 pie shells and bake at 250° for 3 to 40 minutes.

title: ironman cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift/stir together flour, baking powder, and salt.
Set-aside.
In the large bowl of an electric mixer, cream the butter.
Beat in the vanilla and sugars.
Add the eggs and beat well.
On low speed, add the sifted dry ingredients, scraping the bowl and beating only until mixed.
Mix in the oatmeal, wheat germ and coconut.
Then add the chocolate chips and the nuts.

title: apple wraps
directions: Peel apples and cut in quarter slices.
Wrap each piece with canned biscuit.
Be sure to have enough apples for the amount of dough.
Mix sugars, margarine, and water and boil.
Pour over wrapped apples.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: yogurt popsicles
directions: Mix well and freeze in molds.
Insert wooden stick for handle when partially frozen.
Carbohydrate 10 g, protein 3 g, fat 3 g, calories 75.

title: christmas party cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well. Add the slightly beaten eggs and add a little flour into which the chopped nuts have been put. Stir mixture well; add the orange juice and rind.

Add a little more flour and stir again. Add the soda to the buttermilk; stir this into the batter, adding the remainder of the flour as quickly as possible. Bake into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Sift flour, cocoa and baking powder together several times. Set aside.
Separate eggs and beat yolks, vanilla and salt together until light.
Add water and continue beating.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar.
Slowly add flour mixture.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into well-greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn cake out on towel dusted with powdered sugar.
Peel off wax paper and roll up while hot.
When cool, unroll and spread with whipped cream and roll up again.
Spread with chocolate frosting or leave plain.

title: wild rice with almonds and mushrooms
directions: Saute raw rice in butter 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Saute 10 minutes more.
Add chives and pour hot chicken broth over all. Bake in casserole, covered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: chicken with preserves
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper and brown in skillet with the oil.
Place chicken in one layer in casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the chicken so all the poultry is covered with the mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until chicken is brown and gravy has thickened.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Blend milk and egg.
Add gradually to dry ingredients.
Stir in the well drained corn and drop by tablespoon into deep fat (375°).
Fry until golden brown, 4 to 8 minutes, depending on the size.
Drain on paper towels (optional). Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cheddar-bean enchiladas
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, cook ground beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in enchilada sauce, soup, milk and chili peppers.
