Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: italian style chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in dressing for at least 5 hours.
Shake chicken in crumbs, parsley and Parmesan cheese in bag, then bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: old fashion baked macaroni
directions: Beat eggs; add milk and butter and add salt.
Stir well.
Put one layer of macaroni in 8 x 11 1/2 x 2-inch glass casserole dish (approximately 2-quart size).
Put squares of cheese on top of macaroni.
Add 1 more layer of macaroni followed by remaining cheese squares.
Pour milk mixture over all.
Bake in conventional oven 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cannoli
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Cut in with a pastry blender until pieces are the size of small peas.
Mix in shortening and eggs until creamy.
Blend in vinegar and cold water, one tablespoon at a time.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes.

title: spicy oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water, oatmeal and butter.
Cover; let stand 5 minutes.
Beat eggs.
Add brown sugar, beating until smooth.
Mix sifted flour, white sugar, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add egg mixture; mix well.
Then add oatmeal mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured square pan (9 x 12-inch).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or in convection oven 28 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: In a large bowl, soften 1 cake of yeast in 1 1/2 cups of lukewarm water.
Add salt and sugar, then the flour.
Knead the mixture into a soft dough.
Do not let the dough rise.
Cut into small pieces immediately and roll into ropes.
(Do not make the ropes too thick because they swell in baking).
Twist them into pretzel shapes and lay them on a foil-covered cookie sheet dusted with flour.
Brush with beaten eggs.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Makes 3 to 6 dozen pretzels.
Children can make initials with the dough also.

title: barbecued limas
directions: Wash beans; soak overnight in water.
Simmer in same water with salt pork for 2 hours.
Drain; reserve liquid.
Brown onion and garlic in bacon drippings.
Mix seasonings; add to onion and garlic.
Mix thoroughly.
Place beans in baking dish; add 1 1/2 cups of the reserved bean liquid and seasoning.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: raisin pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add pumpkin and baking soda and stir together.
Add egg, flour, spices, salt, nuts and raisins. Mix thoroughly.
Drop by rounded teaspoons on greased baking sheet. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen cookies.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter & sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well. Add milk & dry ingredients.
(Save enough flour to coat fruit.) Cut fruit into fine pieces and coat with flour.
Add fruit to batter and mix.
Drop by tsp onto cookie sheet, 2 inches apart. Bake at 300 degrees for 20-30 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool.
May be frozen.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt oleo and morsels.
Add evaporated milk and powdered sugar. Bring to a boil and boil for 2 or 3 minutes.
Use whisk when adding milk, then sugar.
Lastly, add vanilla.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add crumbled biscuits and raisins, stirring well.
Spoon into greased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Yields 9 servings.

title: canned apples for pie
directions: You can do 3 or 4 gallons of apples at a time.
Just place about a gallon, then sprinkle 1 cup sugar over them and layer other apples and sugar until you have enough.

title: white fudge
directions: Put the sugar and canned milk in a large saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until soft ball stage.
Take off stove.
Add the marshmallow cream, vanilla and oleo.
Beat until thick.
Add the nuts.
Pour into greased pan.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all in blender for 3 minutes.
Grease and flour pan and cook for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Cook giblets and chop into broth.
Add onion, celery and poultry seasoning.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add salt, pepper and egg slices.
Dissolve flour in water before stirring into broth.
Bring to boil and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: speedy caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add brown sugar and cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and continue stirring until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat.
Blend in confectioners sugar gradually.
Add vanilla and mix well. Thin with cream, if necessary.
Frost the cooled cake.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Sift flour and salt into mixing bowl.
Add egg and using half of shell, measure two shell halves full of milk; pour into mixture.
Mix well.
Flour counter; turn dough out onto counter and dust with flour.
Roll out until thin, dusting and flipping dough several times.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Dust well with flour and fold in half.
Dust and fold again and then one more time. Cut in narrow strips and open on counter to dry (2 hours).
Cook in broth about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together with blender.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple loaf
directions: Mix ingredients in the usual manner.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350° in a loaf pan.

title: pasta salad nicoise with california avocado
directions: In a small bowl, combine dressing, basil, garlic and red pepper flakes; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine macaroni, albacore, tomato, avocado, red onion and olives.
Add dressing and toss.
Line four plates with lettuce leaves and spoon on salad. Makes 4 servings.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Marinate the shrimp at least 2 hours in the combined recipe. Cut shrimp up back to devein.
Cook on grill over low heat. Shrimp will turn pink and start to pull off shell.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix in saucepan vinegar, sugar, salt, turmeric and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over slaw while hot.
Stir well. Chill overnight.
This will keep for several days.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash, add all ingredients, mix well. Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients together and shape into small balls. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Scrub potatoes and dry.
Prick skin with fork in several places to allow steam to escape.
Place on oven rack.
Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour or until potatoes feel soft when touched.
Remove.

title: cajun rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Completely cover sausage with water and cook until done.
Combine rest of ingredients with rice, sausage and water.
Put in baking dish. Water should almost cover entire mixture.
Add more if needed. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix and bake in 2-inch pans.
Cool on rack, then split cake crossway (side to side).
Mix sour cream, frozen coconut and sugar in bowl together.
Stack cake with frosting between each layer.
Any leftover frosting and mix in 1 small package coconut, Cool Whip and cover entire cake.
This is best if frozen for about 2 days before serving.

title: angel pie
directions: Mix nuts, flour and butter and then press in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar, then spread on top of first layer.
Spread on instant butter pecan pudding.
Place Cool Whip on top, then sprinkle nuts on.

title: peach pudding
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 1 cup syrup for sauce.
Place peaches in baking dish.
Put bread crumbs over peaches.
Beat together eggs, cream, butter, sugar and cinnamon; pour over bread crumbs. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Prepare Sauce; pour over pudding. Serve while warm.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly and chill.

title: lazy day pot roast
directions: Spread dry soup mix over the roast, the wrap securely in heavy duty foil. Seal foil tightly and place in shallow roasting pan. Bake at 275 degrees for 5 1/2 hours or a little longer won't hurt. When you open package the roast will be floating in a delicious brown juice. This can be thickened slightly for a gravy. Can be served over noodle or rice.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover first 3 items with ice for 1/2 hour.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Add cucumber mix.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Put in jars and seal.

title: sausage balls
directions: Work together Bisquick and sausage until blended.
Mix in grated cheese and roll into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool before freezing, then heat 10 to 12 minutes.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Mix Karo syrup, peanut butter and sugar in large saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Add cornflakes, stir until well coated.
Place in large buttered pan. Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: taco pie
directions: Bake pie shell for 10 minutes at 400°.
Fry ground beef with onion.
Add taco mix according to directions.
Mix refried beans, 3/4 cup cheese, picante sauce, and 10 crumbled Nacho chips, together with beef.
Pour into pie shell and top off with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20-25 minutes.

title: pickle peaches
directions: Peel a dishpan full of peaches in the evening.
Pour a mixture of sugar and cider vinegar over peaches.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Add 1/2 box whole cloves and cook until peaches pierce easily and have a clear look.
Put peaches, while very hot, into sterilized jars, adding 3 cloves per quart with juice.
Seal with hot lids.

title: summer squash
directions: Wash and slice squash in rounds.
Place in salt water or steam.
Drain.
Combine soup (no water) and sour cream.
Stir in carrots.
Fold squash and onion.
Combine stuffing and margarine. Put 1/2 down in 9 x 13-inch pan, then spoon mixture over.
Put remaining stuffing mix and margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab meltaways
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Spread on muffins that have been sliced in half.
Cut each muffin into four sections.
Broil until bubbly and brown.
Serve hot.

title: barbecue sauce with cocoa
directions: First, melt margarine.
Add
onion
rings;
cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Add all other
ingredients.
Bring
to
a slow boil. Cut heat down and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour over meat and cook to your desire in
oven
at
Good for chicken, pork chops, beef or pork ribs.
Also,
can put sauce over rice or mashed potatoes.
Serves 4 people.

title: frozen orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add sherbet, stirring until melted.
Add marshmallows.
Allow mixture to cool.
Stir fruit into gelatin mixture and fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into individual molds or a 5-cup mold.
Freeze.
To serve, unmold onto lettuce leaves.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook apples and water on medium heat until bubbly, then cut back to medium-low.
Cook until they mash up.
After they cook up, run them through the sieve and measure out 8 cups.
Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook for 4 hours with the lid on. Cook another 2 hours with the lid off; stir occasionally.
Put in jars and let cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, soup, onion and rice together and pour into a lightly greased baking dish.
Add half of the cheese and mix.
Put into a 400° oven for 10 minutes or until cheese begins to melt. Add remaining cheese and butter; mix.
Put back in the oven for another 10 minutes.
Keep checking and stirring until all the cheese is melted and well blended.
Cook for 30 more minutes, until top is slightly golden.

title: banana-strawberry frost beverage
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until smooth.
Serve chilled or over ice.
Yields 3 cups.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over crumbs.
Top with chips.
Press down firmly.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: granny hutchinson's cucumber sticks
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime 24 hours.
Soak overnight in alum; rinse and soak 5 or 6 hours in vinegar and sugar mixture.
Cook until clear and put in jars.

title: salmon ball
directions: Blend salmon with cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, horseradish, salt and liquid smoke.
Roll into one big ball and cover with nuts.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Surround with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Pour milk into saucepan and begin heating while preparing other ingredients.
Reserve 1/4 cup of milk to mix with flour, sugar, salt, eggs, cocoa, vanilla and butter.
Slowly pour this mixture into hot milk, stirring well to prevent scorching.
Cook until stiff.
Cool and pour into baked crust.
Cover with meringue and bake until golden brown.

title: turkey salad
directions: Combine turkey, cranberries, celery and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and toss gently.
Can be used for sandwiches or salads.

title: chocolate tart
directions: Mix flour, margarine and chopped nuts together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and let cool.
Add a layer of the banana slices.
Mix together the Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese and spread over the bananas.
Mix both puddings together according to package directions and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Let pudding set and then top with more Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Cream margarine and 1/3 cup sugar.
Add 1 egg, then flour.
Mix well.
Press on bottom and 2-inches up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Cook until thick.
Then add 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
Fill 7 quart jars 1/3 full of sauce and fill jar with apples and process in boiling water for 20 minutes.
Pour 1-quart in unbaked pie shell for pie.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 400°
or until brown.

title: almond cookies
directions: Mix honey, egg, juice, rind, salt, baking powder, and cinnamon.
Add flour, slivered almonds and mix well.
Make several rolls and put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cut immediately.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Cook until candy forms soft ball in cold water.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into pan.
Mix last 3 ingredients and pour over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until light brown.

title: very easy brisket
directions: Combine seasoning in bowl and mix well.
Set brisket on a large piece of heavy foil.
Rub seasons on both side of meat. Wrap tightly in foil.
Set in shallow roasting pan, fatty side up. Let stand 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Place on center rack for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 225° and cook it 8 hours.
Drain off drippings and let cool for 30 minutes.
Slice thinly across the grain.
Serve with your favorite barbecue sauce.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° until done and tester comes out clean.

title: grandma peggy's black bottom pie
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Cook in double boiler until it coats a spoon. Scald milk and add beaten egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar to which cornstarch has been blended.

Pour custard you just made with chocolate chips. Stir until smooth. Add vanilla; stir and pour into baked pie shell. Add softened gelatin to remaining custard. Stir; cool in refrigerator until cool but NOT set.

Beat egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar (add sugar when whites begin to thicken). Fold cooled custard into egg white mixture. Pour over cooled chocolate layer. Let sit at least 2 hours. Cover with whipped heavy cream. Garnish with grated unsweetened chocolate, if desired.

title: do not peek chicken
directions: Sprinkle rice evenly in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted butter and water over rice.
Mix onion soup mix with the 2 soups and spoon over rice.
Lay chicken pieces over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with aluminum foil and seal.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Do not peek.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix together ground round, eggs, bread crumbs and 1 1/2 cans French onion soup.
Make into 6 to 8 (1/4-inch thick) patties. Brown in skillet over medium heat.
Drain off excess grease.

title: brunswick stew from a can
directions: Place all ingredients in pot or Dutch oven.
Simmer for one hour.
Serve.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients according to the above list; top with dressing and marinate 3 to 5 hours.
Toss and serve.

title: green bean parmesan casserole
directions: Cook beans according to package instructions and drain.
Layer beans, mushrooms, oregano, Parmesan cheese and onion rings (in that order) in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour cream over entire casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yummy!

title: mother's raisin cookies
directions: Cook white raisins in 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook until 1/2 cup water is left.
Sift flour.
Add soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Add 1/4 cup water (left from cooking raisins) and nuts.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Spread powdered sugar icing on cookies while still warm.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put hash browns in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over the potatoes.
Mix the soup, sour cream, onion, cheese, salt and pepper together.
(This will be thick.)
Pour mixture over potatoes and butter.
Melt the other stick of margarine and mix with the corn flakes.
Layer on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef ball
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and microwave for 2 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: low-fat chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender and reserve broth. Debone and cut to bite
size
pieces.
Put
in
oil	sprayed 12 x 7-inch baking dish. Defat broth.	Mix with soup.	Pour over chicken. Mix	flour, baking
powder,
milk
and melted margarine until smooth. Spoon on	top of chicken mixture. Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt brown sugar and oleo over low heat, then cool.
Next put in container with tight fitting lid or plastic bag that can be sealed.
Put one can of biscuits at a time into sugar-spice mix and shake until well coated.
Arrange in greased Bundt or tube pan.
Do this until all cans are used.
Pour melted mixture over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Put on platter.

title: apple cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter and grease a 9-inch square pan. Mix flour, brown sugar, sugar, 2 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon, salt and ginger in large bowl.
Add oil; stir until mixture is like coarse meal.
Transfer 3/4 cup of mixture in small bowl.
Reserve for topping.
Stir remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon into mixture in small bowl.
Mix baking powder and baking soda with flour mixture. Add apples.
Whisk buttermilk and egg in another small bowl to blend.
Add apple mixture; stir just until combined.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle reserved topping evenly over.
Bake cake until tester inserted into center comes out clean, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Transfer to rack; cool slightly.
Serve coffee cake warm or at room temperature.

title: chicken curry java
directions: Measure and prepare all ingredients and set by the stove.
Set wok over medium heat; add oil and all ingredients (except chicken and rice).
Mix well, cover and simmer on low for no more than 15 minutes.
Ladle out 1 cup of the liquid and reserve for an added serving sauce.
Make the rice in the meantime.
Remove the mixture from the wok and set aside.
Add more oil to the wok with a bit more curry, if desired.
Add chicken and cook through lightly over high heat.

title: chicken and rice a la costa rica
directions: Cook chicken in water with salt, pepper, celery, a bit of bell pepper and a garlic bud.
(These are not the chopped ingredients listed.)
Save the broth.
Remove chicken from broth and cool. Remove from bone and break into small pieces; set aside.

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift flour and sugar, cut in butter.
Press mixture in ungreased glass pan (13 x 9 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove and cool slightly.

title: tuna divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Place broccoli in a shallow baking dish.
Arrange tuna over broccoli.
Combine soup, milk, cheese and lemon juice.
Pour over tuna.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: spinach rice salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and refrigerate 2 hours. Yield:
about 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine all ingredients and pour into 1-quart casserole. Bake for about 20 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; mix thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating vigorously.
Add vanilla.
Mix to first mixture; knead thoroughly.
Roll out to approximately 1/4-inch thickness; cut out with cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° until lightly or golden brown.
Freezes well.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery until transparent.
Add broccoli and cook until it just separates.
Add other ingredients and mix well in pan.
Pour mixture in 8 x 8-inch casserole dish and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini jam(freezer style)
directions: Boil zucchini 15 minutes or until tender.
Add lemon juice and Sure-Jell; bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O, pineapple and sugar. Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Put in glasses or jars, cool and freeze.

title: red potatoes
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place sliced potatoes and chopped onion in pan and give a toss.
Sprinkle onion powder over; toss again.
Pour milk in.
Cut up butter and place all over mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until tender.

title: beefy squash casserole
directions: Brown beef, bell pepper and onion; drain.
Steam squash or zucchini until just tender, but slightly crunchy.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese, in large bowl.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with grated cheese and bake 10 minutes more or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: turkey loaf(low cholesterol; serves 5)
directions: Mix all together thoroughly.
Pack into loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or pack into microwave-safe round pan; cover with waxed paper and microwave at Medium-high for 14 to 16 minutes.
In either case, let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
In a small skillet, melt margarine. Add onions and pepper.
Saute 5 minutes.
In a buttered 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole dish, put half of noodles, half of onion and pepper mixture, 1 cup cubed cheese, then add corned beef on top of cheese.
Repeat the layers (noodles, onions, peppers and cheese). Stir soup as directed on can with milk.
Pour over casserole.
Add crackers.
Pour 1 tablespoon melted margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sand tarts or ladyfingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar; work in flour, vanilla and nuts.
Form into oblong cookies.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: nutty fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Make in small balls and set in refrigerator to get cold.
Melt wax and chips, then drop balls in chocolate mixture, then put on wax paper.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together except butter, almonds and corn flakes.
(I add a little broth from the boiled chicken.)
Put into 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter, almonds and corn flakes.
Spread mixture on top of casserole. Bake 35 minutes.

title: no crust sweet potato pie
directions: Spray glass pie dish with Pam cooking spray.
Pour mixture in dish and bake in oven for 40 minutes or until it sets good.

title: chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk and onion; mix well. Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles; seal perforations. Spoon 1/4 of chicken mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to center and seal.
Brush tops with melted butter and sprinkle with croutons.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 24 minutes, until golden brown.

title: homemade soap
directions: Make outdoors; use 12-quart enamel pot.
Dissolve Borax and ammonia in water.
Dissolve lye in this mixture, using large stick, stir until dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm and add melted fat. Stir until mixture is thick as fudge.
Pour into box.
Cut when cool.
It floats and is gentle.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak in 1/4-inch strips.
In wok, add oil and steak; stir-fry until meat turns brown.
Add chopped onions, peppers, bouillon, garlic powder, salt and soy sauce.
Cook until onions and peppers are tender.
Mix 1/4 cup soy sauce and cornstarch together.
Add to mixture.
Cook until sauce thickens. May add more soy sauce to your taste.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal and melted margarine; stir in eggs and sweetener. Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix in oatmeal mixture, stirring in alternately with milk and vanilla.
Add raisins.
Drop onto cookie sheet from level teaspoon.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, until golden brown.
Yield:
4 dozen cookies. Carbohydrate 5.6 g, protein 1.1 g, fat 1.6 g, calories 42.
One cookie = 1/4 bread exchange, 1/2 fat exchange, 1/4 fruit exchange.

title: seven layer bean dip
directions: Spread beans in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish or Tupperware.
Spread guacamole over beans, then spread sour cream. Sprinkle cheese, tomato, green onion and olives in layers.
Serve with tortilla chips and/or Fritos.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower in flowerets; cut onion into rings.
Cook bacon crispy and crumble.
Mix mayo, vinegar and sugar together and toss all the above ingredients together.
Mix together and chill before serving.

title: haystacks
directions: Mix syrup and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir remaining ingredients and drop on wax paper to cool.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Chop
pepper
and onions, mix with celery and boil in 4 cups chicken
broth until tender.
Bone and chop chicken. Mix all ingredients
together with 2 cans cream of mushroom soup. Pour
in large baking dish, sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in hot oven until cheese is melted.
Serves 18 to 20 people.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a large glass bowl, spread layer of refried beans.

Mix guacamole (avocado and lemon juice) and spread on top of beans. Mix sour cream with taco seasoning and spread on top of guacamole. Top with sliced olives, grated cheese, diced tomatoes and green onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie shell at 375° for 10 minutes. Layer tomatoes in pie shell, sprinkling each layer with salt, pepper, basil and garlic powder which have been combined. Combine mayonnaise and cheese; spread over tomatoes. May add chopped onion and top with herb dressing mix. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate royale cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on cake box.
Pour into 2 layer pans. Bake and cool.

title: low calorie mock orange julius
directions: Have everything very cold.
Measure into blender.
Blend to mix well.
Add 4 to 6 ice cubes, 1 at a time, until chopped. Blend at high speed for 60 seconds.
Will froth to almost fill 5 cup blender.
Serves 2.

title: sourdough english muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine starter, sugar, salt, water, milk and butter.
Gradually beat in flour until a stiff dough forms.

Turn dough onto floured surface and knead in remaining flour until dough is smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes. Knead in raisins. Shape dough into ball and place in greased bowl. Turn dough, greased-side up. Cover.
Let rise in warm place (80° to 85°F) until dough has doubled in size, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Punch down dough. Sprinkle cornmeal on bread board.
Roll dough to 3/8-inch thickness. turn dough over to coat both sides with cornmeal.
Cut dough into 3-inch rounds. Roll trimming and cut again.

Preheat griddle on setting 5. Cook 6 to 8 muffins at a time 20 to 30 minutes, or until firm and golden brown. Turn every 10 minutes. Repeat with remaining rounds. Serve split and toasted. Yield: About 18 muffins.

title: corn light bread(quick)
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Pour into mixture, leaving a small amount to cover bottom of skillet.
Pour mixture in skillet and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Very good with barbecue.
Also good sliced and toasted.

title: spiced fruit sauce for ham
directions: Drain pineapple and apricots, reserving syrup.
Cut apricots in quarters.
Combine syrups and spices; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove spices.
Combine sugar and cornstarch; stir in small amount of hot syrup, mixing well.
Return to hot mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to boiling.
Add apricots, pineapple and raisins.
Continue cooking 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve warm with ham.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: mrs. mcwaters' cookies
directions: Combine flour, salt and soda.
Sift and set aside.
Combine in a food processor using metal blade the margarine, sugar, brown sugar, egg, salad oil and vanilla.
Combine flour mixture and mixture from food processor into large bowl.
Add oats, corn flakes, pecans and coconut.
Mix all ingredients well.
Place spoonfuls, flattened with a fork or glass bottom, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: sausage squash special
directions: Quarter and cook squash just until tender; drain well and set aside.
Cook sausage with garlic until done; drain.
Add squash; gently mix.
Mix together all dry ingredients and add to sausage and squash.
Gently blend well.
Add Parmesan cheese and milk; mix well.
In a separate bowl beat eggs slightly.
Gently fold into meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with fresh salad and hot rolls!
Enjoy!

title: apple pie(sugar-free)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven until crust is brown (about 30 minutes).

title: peg's punch
directions: Boil the sugar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Cool. When cool, add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemonade.
Stir. Add the mashed bananas.
Stir well and freeze.
When serving, add to cups and fill with 7-Up.

title: grandma elder's salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: date and nut bars
directions: First, melt the oleo in a pan and set aside.

title: italian cream coconut cake
directions: Cream margarine,
Crisco
and sugar; beat until smooth. Add egg yolks and
beat
well.	Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Stir
in	vanilla.
Add
coconut	and
nuts. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.	Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: bacon potato soup
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Crumble and set aside.
Saute onion in small amount of bacon fat.
Add potatoes and water and cook until tender.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Gradually add milk, salt, pepper and parsley.
Add crumbled bacon.
Heat and stir until thoroughly heated, but do not boil.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: maple-spice oat-bran muffins(12 muffins)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray or line 12 muffin cups.
In large mixing bowl, combine bran, baking powder, spices and walnuts.
In another bowl, combine maple syrup and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat liquid ingredients into dry ones and then immediately fold in egg whites.
Spoon into muffin cups at bake 18 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Brown the onion in the vegetable oil; add molasses, ketchup, water, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Put into a crock-pot. Mix together the ground beef, crackers, onion soup mix, milk, salt and pepper.
Form into tiny balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Drain the meatballs and add to the sauce.
Bake on low for 2 hours.
Enjoy!

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream sugars, margarine and Crisco.
Add eggs.
Then add rest of ingredients (alternate with milk).
Add nuts last.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour and 20 minutes in a greased and floured pan.

title: greek style green beans
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes.
Add green beans, seasonings and a few tablespoons of water.
Cover and cook on low heat until beans are tender.
Serves 6.

title: taco pie 2
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of an 8 x 10 1/2-inch dish. Layer chili on top of cheese.
Next, spread peppers on top of chili, then chopped onion on top of peppers.
Spread Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cheese will be melted and bubbly. Serve hot.
Chips should go all the way to bottom to get all the layers on chip.
Great for parties.

title: tossed frito salad
directions: Combine lettuce, onion, tomatoes, beans, salad dressing and cheese. Just before serving, add Fritos.

title: guilt-free snickers snack
directions: Stir this all together and freeze.
Eat frozen.
Reynolds foil midget baking cups are good to freeze in.

title: boerenjones
directions: Wash raisins and cover with lukewarm water for 24 hours.
Add sugar, lemon slices, alcohol and cloves.
Store in a cool, dark place in a sealed container for 3 to 6 months.
Serve in a short glass with a teaspoon.
Makes approximately 1/2 gallon.

title: urso's cocoa mix(yield: enough for a crowd or the winter.)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
For each serving, add 1/3 cup of the mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Place onion, meat, vegetables and then cheese in layers in pie shell.
Mix beaten eggs, milk, dill weed and salt; pour over mix in pie
shell.
Bake
at
for 35 to 45 minutes, until firm. Let set 10 minutes before cutting.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cracker crumbs and margarine. Pour into a greased baking dish; top with melted margarine and cracker crumbs, mixed together. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix together and fill.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple oat bran muffins
directions: In medium bowl stir together first 8 ingredients.
In a small bowl combine milk, egg whites and oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stir just until moist.
Stir in apple.
Spray muffin cups with nonstick spray coating.
Spoon about 1/4 cup batter into each muffin cup.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 12 muffins.
May store batter, tightly covered, in refrigerator for up to 5 days.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread the rolls into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cut-up sausage onto pastry and cover with cheese.
Combine the rest of the ingredients and pour over sausage cheese mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes at 425°.

title: one dish avocado meal
directions: Top avocados with very hot and bubbly chili and top with cheese. Place each serving in microwave for 1 minute to melt cheese more fully. Top with onion, olives, and sour cream.

title: baked chicken and potatoes
directions: Put chicken and potatoes in roasting pan. Add butter, oil and seasonings.
Pour in wine.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour. Remove foil. Raise temperature to 350°.
Cook for 45 minutes or until chicken and potatoes are slightly brown. Turn chicken every 1/2 hour.

title: fresh mushroom salad
directions: Simmer mushrooms in salted water with lemon juice for 10 minutes; drain.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Marinate overnight in the Italian dressing.
Just before serving, drain off dressing as well as possible.
Serve chilled.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Separate rolls and flatten. Place a sausage in each roll and wrap. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix
powdered sugar, cream cheese and pineapple together. Whip
the
whipping cream and fold into mixture.
Pour on graham cracker
crust for 1 pie.
Pour cherry pie filling over that.
Let set overnight.

title: jello dessert
directions: Put jello and cream cheese in a blender.
Add hot water and blend.
In a 9-inch square dish, pour the 7-Up and pineapple (without juice).
Pour the blender mixture over the 7-Up and sprinkle pecans over top.
Refrigerate until stiff and then serve in squares.

title: easy drop cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Drop by scant teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes until light brown.

title: sweet potato pudding(grandmother byrd's)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add egg yolks. Stir in milk and potatoes.
Bake at 375°.
After baking until brown and set, top with the egg whites and brown.

title: lanier's lone star caviar
directions: Drain black-eyed peas well.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Blend in dressing and remaining ingredients and mix well.
Makes about 7 1/2 cups, gets better with time.

title: 6 step pudding dessert
directions: Mix chocolate pudding with 2 cups milk and pour on cream cheese mixture.
Let cool and set up!
Mix vanilla pudding with 2 cups milk and pour on chocolate pudding.
Let cool and set up! Mix pistachio pudding with 2 cups milk and pour on vanilla pudding.
Let cool and set up!
Top with Cool Whip and nuts! Yummy!

title: sweet corn and chicken soup
directions: In a kettle, cook the onion in the butter over moderate heat, stirring, for 4 minutes.
Add the broccoli, the broth, the curry powder and salt and pepper and simmer the mixture, covered, for 30 minutes or until the broccoli is tender.
In a food processor, puree the mixture in batches, transferring the puree to a saucepan. Add the cream and heat the soup over low heat until it is heated through.
Ladle the soup into heated bowls and garnish with the croutons or scallions.
Makes about 8 cups, serving 4 to 6.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Sift flour with salt into a bowl.
Add milk, 2 tablespoons of oil and egg.
Beat until smooth.
Separate onion slices into rings.
Heat cooking oil to hot (375°).

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
In large bowl; combine cooked squash, onion, milk, cheese, melted butter and crushed Ritz crackers. Mix well and spread evenly in a buttered 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 375 degrees for about 30 to 45 minutes or until top is lightly browned.

title: cindy's chocolate fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan, except butter and vanilla.
Cook to a soft ball stage.
Take off heat.
Add butter and vanilla. Whip by hand until starts to fill thick.
Pour into a buttered square 1-quart dish.
Let cool on counter.
Then cut into squares.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugars and margarine; stir in eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add apples and pour into oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle liberally with nuts and brown sugar. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
May be served with whipped cream.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix sugar, milk, margarine and flour together. Put fruit in bottom of dish.
Pour mixture over fruit. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: golden mashed potato bake
directions: This can be made a day ahead (except for baking).
Coat a 3-quart baking dish with cooking spray.
Cook Yukon Gold and sweet potatoes in boiling water in separate pots about 20 minutes or until done.
Beat Yukon Gold potatoes at medium speed with electric mixer until mashed.
Add half the milk, half the cream cheese and half the butter; beat until smooth.
Stir in onions, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into baking dish.
Repeat with sweet potatoes, adding remaining milk, cheese, butter, salt, pepper and thyme.
Spread over Yukon Gold potatoes.
Swirl gently with a knife.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with scallions.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Stir in garlic, oregano and tomato sauce.
Simmer while cooking egg noodles according to package directions.
When noodles are done, drain and stir in sour cream.

title: don't-tell-them-it's low-fat eggnog
directions: In saucepan, heat milk until steaming. Whisk eggs, whites and sugar together in a bowl.
Gradually add and whisk in the hot milk.
Return mixture to saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly with wooden spoon 4 to 6 minutes or until custard thickens enough to coat spoon.
Do not overcook or it will curdle.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for at least 2 hours or better overnight.

title: italian potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until cooked.
Let cool and remove jackets; the cube to bite size pieces.
Add vegetables that have been cubed or sliced.
Fry garlic and spices in oil lightly until hot.
Pour over potatoes and vegetables.
Toss very lightly. Serve warm or cold.

title: plum jam
directions: Stir and cook until thick.
Makes 2 or 3 cups jelly.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Stir in bread cubes, pineapple and milk.
Bake in oblong (greased) baking dish for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 3 layers at 325°. Cool.

title: great grandma davis' chicken pie
directions: Roll out half of the dough and cut in 2-inch strips.
Line a 2-quart ovenproof dish with the strips.
Put chicken, broth, eggs, salt and pepper in dish.
Roll other half of dough and cut in strips.
Place on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: spiced tea(servings:  45)
directions: Combine all ingredients together and store in airtight jar. When ready to serve, put 2 to 2 1/4 teaspoons of tea in a cup and add boiling water.
Mix may be prepared in advance.

title: easy dill-onion bread
directions: In a small mixer bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups of the flour and the yeast.
In a saucepan, heat milk, sugar, butter, dill seed, onion and 1 teaspoon salt just until warm (115° to 120°), stirring constantly to melt butter.
Add to dry mixture; add egg.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in remaining flour.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate together.
Pour all into baked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pillows
directions: Mix cut up, cooked chicken with cream cheese. Add mushrooms. Stuff into rolled out crescent rolls and wrap the roll around chicken mixture. Roll in egg and then bread with crumbs or crushed corn flakes. Place on cookie sheet, leaving room for expansion. Bake according to roll package directions or until golden brown. Top with sauce made from soups and sour cream mixed and warmed in a saucepan. Excellent served with white rice, also topped with sauce.

title: microwave easy zucchini parmesan
directions: In a 1-quart casserole dish, microwave butter or margarine 20-30 seconds on High until melted. Add seasonings and zucchini and stir. Cover loosely with waxed paper and microwave 4-5 minutes on High. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and microwave 1 minute on High. Let stand 2 minutes.

title: ritz pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
In another bowl, beat whites of 3 eggs adding 1/2 cup sugar.
Add to first mixture, mixing well together.
Press out in greased 8-inch Pyrex pie dish, pulling up on side of dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Whip 1 pint of cream. Place on top of pie after it is cold.
Grate bittersweet chocolate over top.
Sweeten cream with 4x sugar to taste.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add spices and eggs.
Sift flour and baking soda into mixture.
Add apples.
Batter will be very thick. Bake 45 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Add pizza sauce, mushrooms and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Mix macaroni and milk in bowl.
Layer ground beef mixture, macaroni mixture, cheese and pepperoni 1/2 at a time in 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Place melted oleo and pretzels in 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake 10 minutes at 400°. Mix cream cheese and sugar; spread over pretzels. Spread Cool Whip over top. Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water. Stir in frozen fruit; let thicken.
Pour over Cool Whip layer. Refrigerate 12 hours. Ready to serve.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread this mixture over the cooled pretzel crust.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine stuffing mix and hot water.
Break sausage into small pieces and add
to	moistened
stuffing
mix.
Stir
in onion, celery, egg and baking powder until evenly distributed. Shape into balls, using
cup
of	mixture
for each ball. Place in baking pan	and
cover
with
foil,
securing tightly around pan. Bake in slow oven at 325° for 15 minutes.
Remove foil;
increase oven
temperature to 350° and continue baking 25 minutes or until sausage is done.
Yields 18 to 22 balls.

title: grandma burgees' butter tarts
directions: Line muffin pans with your favorite pastry.
Cream butter, sugar, corn syrup, salt and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs, milk and nuts or raisins.
Fill shells 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake until firm (about 30 minutes).

title: crab quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie crust as directed on package.
Beat eggs.
Stir in cream, onion, salt and red pepper. Sprinkle crabmeat and cheese in pie crust.
Pour egg mixture over crabmeat and cheese.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake for 15 minutes. Reduce oven to 300°.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: timely trifle
directions: Bake cake according to directions in prepared 9 x 13-inch pan. (May be done the day before.)
Break half the cake into bottom of small punch bowl.
Prepare pudding mix with milk.
Layer half the pudding, 1 can drained pineapple, 2 1/2 bananas and 1 can cherry pie filling over cake.
Mix whipped topping and nuts. Spread half of this over the cherry pie filling.
Repeat layers, ending with nut topping mixture. Decorate with cherries. Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
Juice from the pineapple may be added to your cake mix.

title: 8 can soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add 8 cans.
Let simmer until thick.

title: refrigerated rolls
directions: Mix the warm water with yeast and 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Mix the hot water, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and margarine.
Let cool, then add egg mixture in yeast.
Add about 5 1/4 cups of flour.
Stir to mix in flour.
Turn out on floured board and knead about 10 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl.
Cover and store in refrigerator until doubled in bulk or overnight.
Punch down and shape into rolls.
Let rise and bake at 400° until done.
Keeps well 4 or 5 days.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Slightly soften ice cream; slice over crust.
Sprinkle with Spanish peanuts; freeze.
Melt chocolate chips and oleo.
Stir well and add powdered sugar and evaporated milk.
Cook slowly on medium heat for 15 minutes, stirring.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring. Cool well and pour over ice cream.
Spread with 1 cup Cool Whip. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Keep frozen until 10 minutes before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Pour
milk over soft bread crumbs in a large bowl.
Add melted butter.
Add
grated
melted
cheese, salt and pepper; mix.
Add slightly beaten eggs and macaroni.
Pour in greased 9 x 9-inch shallow pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven
and
add slices of cheese.
Return to oven until cheese has melted. Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute the first 3 ingredients about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick; add 1 cup water.
Cook until thick again.
Add another cup of water until very thick.

title: quiche
directions: Brush pie shell with beaten egg.
Prick and bake 5 minutes at 425° for glass pan or 450° for metal.
Cool on wire rack.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle with cheese in pie shell.
Beat remaining ingredients until well blended. Pour in pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes after baking.
This is important to allow quiche to set.

title: *date nut bread
directions: Combine dates, raisins, soda and boiling water and mix together.
Allow to cool.
Add remaining ingredients to date and raisin mixture, mixing all ingredients together.
Bake in seven greased, unridged cans the size cranberry sauce comes in.
Fill the cans 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Can also use greased bread pans instead of the cans.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve orange and lemon jello in boiling water in bowl.
Add cold water; mix well.
Chill until partially set.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice.
Add pineapple and bananas to gelatin; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Chill until set.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients and spread over cake in pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or longer until top gets soft of brown.

title: butterscotch cream pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Add a small amount to egg yolks and stir into remaining hot mixture.
Cook 1 minute and add vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: gingerbread
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth. Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve plain or top with whipped cream.

title: delma's fruit dip
directions: Mix together until smooth. Very good with apples, orange slices, kiwi, grapes etc.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese; set aside.
Mix pudding according to directions on box.
After pudding mixture thickens, add Cool Whip.
Fold in cream cheese mixture.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften the cream cheese, then mix with sour cream; add the seasoning package.
Blend.
Pour the salsa on top of that; do not mix!
Shred the lettuce, then cover the salsa.
Dice the tomatoes and cover the lettuce.
Then top it all off with the shredded Cheddar cheese.
Grab the chips and dip in!
Yummy!

title: pop eyes
directions: Cut a circle out of the center of a piece of bread (save the circle).
Melt butter or margarine in a pan; put the bread in. Crack an egg into the hole in each slice of bread.
As the bread browns and the egg cooks, turn, if desired.
Brown the circle of bread in a little butter.
Serve for breakfast or lunch.

title: pecan pie
directions: Brown
butter
slightly.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, syrup and one egg at a time.
Beat.
Add pecans.	Bake at 400° until set about 30 minutes.

title: chop suey
directions: Cook meat almost tender.
Add soy sauce and other seasonings and a small amount of water while cooking.
When meat is tender, add onions, celery and green pepper and thicken to desired thickness with cornstarch mixed with 1 cup of cold water.
Simmer only a few minutes.
Add bean sprouts.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: nut log
directions: Mix all this together.
Make into 4 logs.
Roll in coconut. Wrap in wax paper or foil.
Keep in refrigerator.
Can be sliced after it gets cold.
Put in airtight container.

title: jellied peach sauce
directions: Drain peaches, reserving juice and puree in blender.
Add water to juice to make 1 cup liquid.
Pour into saucepan; add sugar and nutmeg.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 1 minute. Empty jello into a bowl and pour in hot liquid.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pureed peaches and pour into mold.
Chill until set.
Serve this instead of cranberry sauce.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Boil macaroni until tender. Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, mix beef, macaroni, pepper and sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: "plains special" cheese ring
directions: Mix
cheese,
nuts,
mayonnaise
and
onion
until well blended in a
bowl; stir in cayenne and black pepper to taste. Pack into a 5 cup ring mold or any 4 cup mold (I shape mixture into a
ring
by
hand).
Chill
overnight until firm.
Unmold onto a
serving plate.
Fill center with strawberry preserves. Serve with crackers.
Makes 4 cups.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add sour cream and soda.
Mix well.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Blend well.
This is a soft dough so it is best to chill for a few hours before rolling out and cutting.
Use any shape cookie cutter.
Good for Christmas and other holidays.
Bake about 12 minutes at 350°.
If desired, tops may be sprinkled with sugar before baking.

title: spicy white bean soup
directions: Cook onion in butter in large Dutch oven.
Add beans and other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes. Yields 3 1/2 quarts.

title: mexican dip
directions: Make in layers in 9 x 13-inch dish as follows:

title: long nut rolls
directions: Mix together yeast and warm water.
Cream sugar, butter and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream, baking powder, yeast mixture and flour.
Mix with hands until no longer sticky. Put in refrigerator overnight.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 1 cup flour together.
Use to roll the dough out on (make more if needed).

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix the first 12 ingredients together.
Steam lightly 2 medium heads of cabbage until leaves can be folded without breaking. Pack the mixture in the leaves.
Cook at a moderate simmer for about 1 1/4 hours or until done.
The juice will come from 1 1/2 to 2-quarts home canned tomatoes.

title: quick zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs, sugar, oil, then vanilla, zucchini and flour mixture.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Grease and flour 9
x 5-inch loaf pan.)

title: kamikaze
directions: Mix in glass over ice or can make in shaker and pour into shots.

title: strawberry angel food cake
directions: Split about 1/2 angel food cake.
Cut inside down to 1/3 at bottom.
Mix cake with strawberry gelatin and frozen strawberries. Fill bottom layer with mixture and place top layer over.
Frost with Cool Whip tinted with red food coloring.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: Mix together the night before, except Cool Whip.
Add Cool Whip before serving.

title: puri (non)(a bread)
directions: Sift the flour and salt; knead it with water to a smooth and slightly stiff dough.
Cover it and keep it for an hour.
Knead again and make small round balls about the size of a lemon.
Roll out each ball into a round 1/2-inch thick and put it in the hot oil.
Press it until it puffs up and then turn it on the other side.
Fry until it turns light brown.
Serve hot with any curry. Serves 7.

title: mario spaghetti
directions: Put water on to boil for spaghetti.
Cut bacon into cubes and brown.
Turn skillet off and add a splash of vinegar.
In a separate bowl, beat an egg.
Beat in 1 can milk, 1/2 can of beef or chicken gravy, 3/4 cup of grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Boil spaghetti and drain.
Turn on bacon fat.
Put spaghetti into skillet.
Give sauce a stir and then pour over and toss like a salad.

title: frozen cream fruit salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese with juice from fruit cocktail.
Add fruit and put into mold.
Freeze.
You can add 1 pint whipped cream before freezing as a dessert.
Serves 10.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix together and store in an airtight container indefinitely. To make one cup: mix 2 teaspoons to a cup of boiling water.
Stir.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt cheese whip and margarine together.
Combine all other ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: better-than-sex cake
directions: Place cake mix, pudding mix, sour cream, milk, oil, butter and eggs in a large mixer bowl.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed, stopping halfway to scrape sides of bowl.
Stir in chocolate pieces, grated chocolate and nuts.
Place in greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack for 25 minutes.
Turn out of pan.
Cool completely on rack.

title: tropical pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at low speed.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Glaze.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, nuts and melted margarine in mixing bowl.
Press into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: shirley's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine ingredients and blend well.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: hot pickle relish
directions: Peel tomatoes, cut in small pieces and drain well.
Add other ingredients chopped fine.
Drain all very carefully.
Add vinegar and seasoning and cold pack.

title: lebkuchen cookies
directions: Bring to boil molasses, 1 cup water, sugar and shortening. Cool.
When cold, add salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, anise oil, baking soda and hot water.
Add 10 to 11 cups flour to make stiff. Let stand overnight in cool place.
Roll out on floured board. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Dough thickens overnight.
To frost, use powdered sugar, salt, hot water and vanilla.
Blend to proper consistency.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour in soups, rice and mushrooms.
Bake for one hour in 350° oven.

title: dressing
directions: Cube loaf of day old bread and sprinkle generously with warm water.
Let stand.
Cook onion in butter until clear.
Over crumbs sprinkle salt, pepper, sage and eggs.
Mix well.
Then add baking powder, onion, celery and giblets.
Stir this well.
Moisten with broth from bird until fairly moist.
Cook 30 minutes in 375° oven.

title: cottage cheese hawaiian
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip, pineapple, marshmallows and coconut until well blended.
Sprinkle 1 package of orange jello over mixture and stir until well blended.
Store in a covered container in refrigerator.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine in large pot for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Stir in broth, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: russian black bread
directions: Combine rye and white flour in a large bowl.
Mix 2 1/3 cups flour mixture, sugar, salt, cereal, caraway seed, coffee, onion powder, fennel seed and undissolved yeast.
In a saucepan, combine 2 1/2 cups water, vinegar, molasses, chocolate and margarine. Heat over low heat until liquids are warm.
(Margarine and chocolate do not need to melt.) Gradually add dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed or by hand.
Stir in dough, additional flour mixture to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Cover dough with bowl and let rest 15 minutes.
(Dough may be sticky.)
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double in size (about 1 hour).
Punch dough down.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Divide in half.
Shape into balls about 5-inches in diameter.
Place each ball in a greased 8-inch round pan.
Cover; let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Meanwhile, combine cornstarch and 1/2 cup cold water, stirring constantly over medium heat until mixture boils.
Continue stirring constantly for 1 minute.
As soon as bread is baked, brush mixture over top of loaves.
Return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes or until glaze is set.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: hotsy-totsy dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and chill.
May be served with tortillas, nachos, chips or pretzels.

title: fruit salad squares
directions: Drain fruits and reserve 1 cup syrup.
Combine syrup in saucepan with sugar, cornstarch, gelatin, salt and orange and lemon juices.
Cook until thickened and boil for 2 minutes.
Add a small amount of this to beaten egg.
Return to hot mixture and cook 1 minute longer.
Cool to room temperature and fold in the fruits, marshmallows, nuts and topping.
Use a 9 x 9-inch dish. Cool.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Cut in squares.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion until tender.
Blend in flour and chicken broth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in rice, ham, carrots, almonds and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Blend in half and half and sherry.
Serve warm, garnishing with parsley or chives.

title: holiday spiced punch
directions: Heat and stir the red hots in the water until dissolved.
Cool. Add the juices.
If the red hots do not sweeten the punch to desired taste, add a little sugar.
Makes 22 (6 ounce) servings or 16 (8 ounce) servings.

title: eight layer salad
directions: Cut and layer vegetables in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer the peas last.
Layer the mayonnaise over peas.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Fry bacon and drain.
Crumble over top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: smores
directions: Spread graham crackers with Marshmallow Creme and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
To with another graham cracker.
Put into a 200° oven for 2 to 4 minutes, until chocolate chips are melted. Cool and enjoy.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers with salt.
Let stand 3 hours.
Do not pour off brine.
Mix all together onions, sugar, mustard seed, celery seed, turmeric, cloves and pimientos.
Cover with vinegar.
Let cook about 5 minutes after it comes to a boil.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Boil the squash and onion in lightly salted water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine the cream of chicken soup and sour cream; stir into drained squash mixture.
Combine the bread crumbs and melted butter; spread 1/2 in baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture over crumbs; sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: gravy water
directions: Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Strain well.
Reserve liquid!
Discard vegetables and use liquid to make gravy.

title: mom's chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine butter, milk, cocoa and sugar in large pot.
Heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add vanilla, oats and nuts.
Stir well.

title: garlic chicken kiev
directions: Mix margarine, chives and garlic powder; shape into rectangle, 3 x 2-inches.
Cover and freeze until firm, about 30 minutes. Remove excess fat from chicken; flatten each chicken breast half to 1/4-inch thickness between waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Heat oven to 425°.
Cut margarine mixture crosswise into 6 pieces.
Place 1 piece on center of each chicken breast.
Fold long sides over margarine; fold up ends and secure with wooden pick.
Mix cornflakes, parsley and paprika.
Dip chicken into buttermilk; lightly and evenly coat with cornflake mixture.
Place chicken breasts, seam side down, in square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches, sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake uncovered until chicken is done, about 35 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add chocolate and stir over low heat until chocolate is melted.
Add boiling water gradually, stirring constantly; heat to boiling.
Add sugar and syrup, stirring until dissolved.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and salt.
Serves 6.

title: whipped cream icing
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Let cool.
Cream thoroughly Spry, butter and sugar.
Combine all ingredients and beat in mixer 5 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: almond brickle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box using stick of butter instead of amount in mix directions.
Add 1 teaspoon of almond extract and 1/2 of packaged pudding mix.
Bake in stem pan according to mix directions.
Let cool.
Whip the cream with 2 tablespoons sugar, 1 teaspoon almond extract and rest of pudding mix until stiff.
Ice with this mixture.
Sprinkle Bits 'O Brickle and almond slices on top.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except soda and popcorn in 1 1/2 to 2-quart dish.
Bring to a boil in microwave oven, and then cook for 2 minutes on full power.
Remove from microwave and stir in soda.
Put popcorn in grocery bag; pour syrup over popcorn.
Close bag and shake.
Cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake and cook another 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour out and let cool.

title: pineapple banana delight
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients together in a double boiler, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.
Chill!
Just before serving, add remaining ingredients.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, 1 pint cold water and sugar for 20 minutes. Dissolve 2 envelopes Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water and stir into cranberries while hot.
Cool and add the pineapple, nuts and celery.
Put in refrigerator and let set.

title: chicken kabobs
directions: Combine 8 ingredients listed after chicken, mix well.
Add chicken.
Cover and marinate at least 2 hours in refrigerator. Remove chicken.
Reserve marinade.
Alternate chicken, pineapple and vegetables on skewers.
Grill 6 inches from medium-hot charcoal for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Turn and baste often with marinade.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sauteed chicken breast
directions: Spread flour on a piece of wax paper; dredge each chicken breast.
Melt the butter and oil in a skillet.
When it foams, add chicken.
Cook over medium-high heat for about 3 minutes on each side.
Remove to a warm platter.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of fat from pan.
Stir in lemon juice, salt and pepper.
When very hot, spoon this sauce over chicken and sprinkle with parsley.

title: chocolate snickerdoodles
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add small amounts to creamed mixture.
Roll dough into balls, then roll in sugar.
Place balls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet-n-sour meat balls
directions: Heat catsup and jelly together until well mixed.

title: classic chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water; drain.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add chicken broth, stirring until thick.
Stir in cream, sherry, salt and pepper.
Place broccoli crosswise in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour 1/2 the sauce over broccoli; top with chicken slices.
Add Parmesan cheese to remaining sauce; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Broil until sauce is golden.

title: perfect chicken casserole
directions: Blend soup and milk in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add chicken, noodles, pimento and parsley.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: nondairy cheese sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Good over cauliflower and broccoli; can be used for a dip.

title: brocoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13 inch casserole dish and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach or berry cobbler
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients together for 5 minutes, stirring gently, very often.
Set aside.
Melt butter in 8-inch square pan or deep dish that is ovensafe.
Combine sugar, milk and flour. Stir and pour into pan over butter.
Then pour fruit mixture on top of flour mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together in large bowl.
Sift and add flour, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix well. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Can add raisins and nuts, if desired.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Mix potatoes with sugar; add coconut, milk, eggs and spices and blend.
Pour into greased casserole pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Pour marshmallows on top.
Brown until melted.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt white chocolate squares in double boiler.
Add peanut butter.
Spread on aluminum foil on a cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Swirl this into white chocolate mixture.
A marbleized effect is made.
Refrigerate until hardened, then break into pieces.

title: moo goo gai pan
directions: Add tablespoon oil to wok; heat on medium high.
Add snow peas, mushrooms and onions; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove from wok and set aside.
In small cup, mix the cornstarch, salt, ginger and pepper; set aside.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons oil to wok.
Add chicken and cornstarch mixture; stir-fry until chicken turns white.
Stir in snow pea mixture and soy sauce; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery soup

title: cheese roll
directions: Put 1/4 ham in cheese roll.
Roll cheese roll in remainder of ham.

title: orange delight cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and orange rind. Beat until smooth.
Add milk to soda.
Add flour and salt to baking powder.
Fold in nut meats.
Bake at 350°.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: cherries delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or golden brown; cool.
Blend powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip and spread over cooled crust.
Top with 2 cans of cherry pie filling.
Keep refrigerated until ready to use.

title: corn meal griddle cakes
directions: Scald meal with enough boiling water to cover it.
Let stand 5 minutes, then add flour and salt.
Thin to a batter with beaten egg and milk.
Add baking powder last, beating it in well.
Cook at once on hot, well-greased griddle.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate sweetheart cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8-inch square baking pan.
In a medium bowl, stir together flour, sugars, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla; beat with a whisk until smooth.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven 18 to 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Transfer to cutting board.
Using 3 1/4-inch heart-shaped cookie cutter, cut cake into four pieces.
Spread chocolate frosting on top of two pieces.
Place remaining two hearts on top.
Garnish with decorator icing.
Makes 2 small cakes.

title: rose's cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the cream cheese, eggs, 1 1/2 cups sugar and vanilla.
Batter will be lumpy.
Divide batter into the 3 crusts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts. Take cooked chicken and set aside to cool. Cook vermicelli in chicken broth, then drain. Saute onions and peppers in margarine. Set aside. Chop chicken and Velveeta. Add to vermicelli. Add onions, peppers, mushrooms and peas. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet. Drain off fat. Add onions, salt, pepper, 1/2 teaspoon seasoning and one can of tomato paste. Blend well. Open can of crescents, unroll and separate dough into 8 triangles. Place in ungreased 9-inch pie plate, pressing pieces together to form a crust. Turn meat mixture into unbaked crust. Top with cheese slices. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Beat chicken between pieces of wax paper with flat side of meat cleaver until 1/4-inch thick.
Arrange slice of ham and cheese on inside of each chicken breast.
Roll and secure with a toothpick. Dip rolled chicken in mixture of beaten eggs and oil, then roll in bread crumbs.
Arrange in pan and cook at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: one dish dinner
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain.
Combine rest of ingredients with beef and onion.
Stir until cream cheese is smooth.
Pour into greased 2 quart casserole dish and bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Top with biscuits and continue to cook until biscuits are done.
(Optional:
Put sliced olives on biscuits.)

title: smoked turkey salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill to blend flavors about 1 hour. Makes about 4 cups.

title: cream cheese dainties
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese; then add sugar and extract and cream until fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add to butter/cheese/sugar mixture.
Beat until just mixed, cover and chill dough.
Roll into balls.
Roll in crushed walnuts and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Then press 1/2 glaced cherry in top of each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Gently heat all ingredients, except crab.
When smooth, add drained crabmeat.
Serve with crackers.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni according to directions on package, adding a little oil to keep it from boiling over.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients together. Place in baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Dust with paprika.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients; batter will be slightly runny.
Roll on lightly floured surface until dough reaches a smooth consistency. Cut 3/4-inch thick.
Melt 1/2 stick butter on cookie sheet.
Place biscuits slightly touching.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Brush with melted butter immediately after baking.

title: crescent sausage squares
directions: Add pimento at Christmastime for color!

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Mix all together uncooked and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix and press into bottom and sides of pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: those potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in jacket the night before using.
Do not overcook.
Cool and refrigerate.
Next day, peel, shred (do not grate) into shallow baking dish (7 x 12 x 2-inch).
Arrange lightly in dish.
Add salt and cheese.
Pour cream over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until brown. These can be prepared early in the day.
Cover and refrigerate, then pour over cream just before putting in oven.

title: gingerbread mix dough
directions: Will also need a bowl, plastic wrap and a greased cookie sheet.

title: spinach balls
directions: Leave dressing crumbly, do not crush.
Undercook spinach; drain well and cool.
Combine with all other ingredients and mix well.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Freeze.
After solid, store in plastic bag in freezer.

title: quick, crisp pickles
directions: Pour over drained cukes and onions. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat immediately and pack in hot jars. Seal. Yield: about 8 pints.

title: grammie's hermits
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Stir dry ingredients together.
Combine milk and molasses.
Add alternately to the sugar and oil.
Stir in raisins.
Spread evenly over a large greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cut into squares or bars while still warm.
Cool on racks.

title: cavatelli and broccoli
directions: Bring large 6-quart pot of water to boil.
Add cavatelli to boiling water.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add cut-up broccoli.
Cook for another 10 minutes.
Drain cavatelli and broccoli.

title: old fashion peanut brittle
directions: Stir together in 2 qt. bowl sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave on high for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts, stir well and microwave for 4 minutes on high.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir well and microwave on high for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir gently until light and foamy.
Pour mixture at once onto heavy duty foil. Spread thin with a wooden spatula.
Color will change to a rich golden brown.

title: tuna patties
directions: Mix ingredients and form into patties.
In skillet over medium heat, brown the patties for about 5 minutes on each side.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Brown and crumble sausage; drain grease and set aside.
Melt Velveeta until smooth.
(Works great in crock-pot.)
Add sausage and tomatoes and mix well.
Serve as dip with tortilla chips.

title: quick sweet whole wheat bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Combine egg, molasses, brown sugar, vegetable oil and lemon peel.
Add the flour mixture alternately with yogurt or buttermilk to the ingredients.
Pour into a greased pan and bake about 50 minutes.
Makes a 9 x 5-inch loaf.

title: zucchini orange bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom only of two 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
In large bowl, beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar gradually.
Stir in oil, orange juice and zucchini.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Level off.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except glaze.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pans, cool slightly.

title: salmon caesar
directions: In medium bowl, beat together eggs, milk and soup.
Stir in croutons, salmon, green pepper and onion.
Pour into buttered 11 3/4 X 7 1/2 X 1 3/4 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and bake at 350 for 45 minutes or until center is set.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter; cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly to boiling; bring to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and immediately add Marshmallow Fluff and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish or smaller size and let set. Freezes well.

title: philly summer freeze
directions: Combine crumbs and butter and press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Place in freezer for 15 minutes.

title: cherry delight pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well until thickened.
Fold whipped topping into mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell or graham cracker crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: bean-pea salad
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, pepper and salad oil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add dressing to peas and beans; bring to a boil.
Add a few slices of onion.
Let stand in refrigerator for 2 hours. Drain before serving.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: toll house cookies with oatmeal
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.

title: lemon rice chicken orient
directions: Brown chicken in peanut oil and butter; remove.
Set aside.
To oil add rice, water chestnuts, green onions, ginger, garlic, lemon rind and spices.
Cook, stirring 1 minute.
Add chicken broth, lemon juice and soy sauce; bring to boil.
Arrange chicken on top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes (until liquid is absorbed).

title: easy caramel dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
