Add brown sugar and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Serve with apple slices or popcorn.

title: fabulous fish in foil
directions: Thaw fillets if frozen.
Divide into 4 portions; sprinkle each with 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cook mushrooms in butter until tender but not brown.
Stir in sherry and onion.
Mix cornstarch and water until smooth; stir into mushroom mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in lemon juice and parsley.

title: german fruit cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour (less 1/4 cup), allspice, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to first mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Fold in cherry, apricot and pineapple preserves.
Dredge pecans in 1/4 cup flour and fold into mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in angel food cake pan.

title: charlotte's webb
directions: This drink can be made virgin by leaving out the Frangelico. Will also need coffee glass.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, salt and spices to a boil.
Pour hot over zucchini and onions.
Let stand 1 hour.
Bring to a boil. Cook 3 minutes.
Put in jars and seal at once.
Makes 6 pints.

title: lokshen kugel
directions: Drop noodles in rapidly boiling salted water.
Cook until tender.
Drain in a colander.
Beat eggs with sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Add the noodles.
Melt shortening in baking dish and add to mixture.
Turn half the mixture into baking dish; sprinkle with raisins and nuts.
Top with remaining mixture.
Top with crumbs and bake for 45 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: boiled custard
directions: Separate eggs.
Mix egg yolks, sugar and whipping cream (just as it is, from carton, not whipped).
Place container over boiling water and cook until coats a spoon.
Remove and cool, then add flavorings to taste.

title: pasta with mushrooms
directions: Drain tomatoes; set aside.
Cook pasta according to directions, omitting salt.
Drain and set aside.
Place chicken broth in large skillet; bring to a boil.
Add mushrooms, shallots and garlic. Cook uncovered over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add tomato, basil and ground pepper.
Cook, covered, 10 minutes.
Add reserved pasta, pepper strips and Parmesan cheese.
Stir well.
Cover and cook an additional 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve immediately.

title: black and white brownies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and vanilla and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Add salt and flour and mix well.
Divide batter in halves.
Add chocolate to one half and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, alternating batters, into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Swirl with a knife to marbleize.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost and top with nuts, if desired.
(Nuts may also be added to batter.)

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine together the pretzel sticks, butter and sugar.
Spread in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Let cool.

title: peach dumplings
directions: Roll out each biscuit thin.
Fill each one with peaches and place on greased baking dish.

title: pizza dough
directions: Add yeast to warm water.
Let rise 2 hours.

title: old fashioned beef soup
directions: Saute beef cubes in shortening until brown.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook slowly for 2 hours in a large pot on the stove.
For extra liquid, use 2 cans of tomato soup and 2 cans of beef broth.

title: batter for fried chicken
directions: Combine.
Dip cut up chicken pieces and fry in oil.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Mix flour, cinnamon, soda, sugar and salt.
Add oil, pineapple, eggs, vanilla and bananas.
Stir just enough to mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: carrot broccoli casserole
directions: Defrost broccoli and carrots.
Spread into a casserole dish coated with Pam spray.
Mix milk and soup; pour over vegetables. Mix margarine with corn flakes; top with vegetables.
Sprinkle paprika over the top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until thoroughly cooked.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Bake cake.
Set aside.
Bring to a boil pineapple and sugar. Place on top of cake while hot.
Set aside to cool.
Prepare instant pudding and spread on top of pineapple mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts and coconut.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until lightly browned.
Add broth, water and wine.
Simmer until onions are tender.
Add croutons and sprinkle with cheese.

title: cheese chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: cream of anything soup
directions: Saute butter and flour; add milk.
This makes a thick white sauce, if cheese is added, add here and whisk to melt.
Mix in cooked vegetables or meat and stir until smooth.
Add broth to desired consistency.
Season to taste.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach for 5 minutes and drain well.
Mix ingredients and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Shape into balls and bake at 350° for twenty minutes on a lightly greased cookie sheet.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Cut sour cream into biscuit mix.
Add Sprite or 7-Up.
Mix thoroughly.
Knead dough well.
Roll or cut biscuits.
Place in oiled pan (an iron skillet makes great biscuits).
Dip tops in oil before placing in pan.
Bake at 425° to 450° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rice dressing
directions: Mix well; put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
(Can be used with eggplant.)

title: night before casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Put vegetables in casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over vegetables. Blend the rest of ingredients in blender for 2 1/2 minutes.
Pour mixture over vegetables and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife stuck in center comes out clean.

title: salmon patties
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Be sure mixture is thick.
Make into patties.
Put in hot oil.
Cook on medium heat until golden brown.

title: mother's lime salad
directions: Combine in order given.
Refrigerate until served.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Combine all ingredients except the salad oil in 1-quart bowl. Beat thoroughly.
Add salad oil, one teaspoon at a time, beating well after each addition.
After all the salad oil has been added, beat one more minute or until mayonnaise is thick enough to hold its shape when spooned out.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups mayonnaise.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Mix all except 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into baking dish; sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese and paprika on top.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Blend pudding and milk with whipping cream.
Spread between layers.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: mushroom pie
directions: Clean and slice mushrooms.
Saute with onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Add flour, stir and cook 2 minutes.
Gradually stir in light cream, sherry, salt and pepper.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Add top crust.
Slit to release steam.
Bake at 425° until brown, about 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Excellent buffet dish.

title: hamburger oriental casserole
directions: Brown together hamburger, celery and onions; drain.
Mix all other ingredients together and place in covered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 15 minutes longer. Serve over chow mein noodles.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Combine oil, eggs and strawberries.
Stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Pour batter into two greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake bread in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars together. Add eggs and the remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cut up onion (thin).
Put in skillet with 3 tablespoons butter.
Salt lightly.
Put onion aside when done.
Leave remaining butter.
Cut up carrots in 2-inch sticks.
Use 1 tablespoon butter.
Put in skillet on medium for about 15 to 20 minutes or until carrots are soft.
Then mix the parsley, lemon and onion in with carrots.
Toss until all is mixed on low heat, approximately 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, cooked noodles and broth.
Add chicken. Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top, then sprinkle 1/2 cup grated cheese on top of that.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: orange beef sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place a 2 pound flank steak into mix and refrigerate overnight or longer.
Grill steak.
Heat up mixture that's left and pour over sliced steak.
Also great with noodles.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mix ingredients and place in greased baking dish.
Cover with 1 cup gravy and hot creamed potatoes.
Brown as for a meringue. Ingredients may also be placed in a double pie shell and baked as a pie.

title: jerry's strawberry pie
directions: Boil the water, sugar and cornstarch together until thick. Add Jell-O and food coloring.
Let cool.
Place strawberries in baked pie shell and pour the filling on them.
Top with Cool Whip if desired.

title: ambrosia cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add other ingredients and blend well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Combine water, soy sauce, cornstarch, bouillon and garlic powder and set aside.
Preheat 10-inch browning microwave dish at High for 5 minutes.
Add oil, onions, chicken and broccoli.
Stir until stops sizzling.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes, or until chicken is no longer pink.
Add mushrooms and soy sauce mixture and stir.
Microwave, covered, 2 to 3 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Serve over rice or Rice-A-Roni. Low-fat and low calories.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until tender-crisp. Drain and run under cold water.
Combine other ingredients.
Mix well.
Add carrots and marinate overnight.

title: flaming fruit cocktail
directions: Prepare your favorite fruit salad; chill.
Spoon into crystal sherbet-champagne stemware.
Soak sugar cubes in lemon extract for 2 to 4 minutes.
Remove sugar cubes from lemon extract and place 1 in center of each individual serving.
Place one fruit cocktail in center of each place setting.
When guests are seated light sugar cube with a match.

title: alto octavo omelette
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Place yolks, milk, salt, pepper, parsley, mushrooms and cheese in blender; blend 15 seconds.
Fold yolk mixture into beaten whites.
Pour into large, buttered skillet.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 40 minutes, or until golden brown and puffed.
Yields 4 servings.

title: party bread
directions: Want something different from garlic bread?
Make Party Bread. Cut French bread in slices almost to the bottom of loaf.
Mix together the mayonnaise, cheese, Worcestershire sauce and onions. Spread on French bread in between slices.
Wrap entire loaf in aluminum wrap and bake 30 minutes at 300° to 350°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 30 minutes in a moderate oven at 350°.

title: papa john's quick and spicy sauce
directions: In small saucepan, saute garlic in oil until golden.
Add tomatoes, basil, salt, whole pepper and black pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Cook spaghetti per box directions.
Remove when firm.
Toss and mix with sauce. Serve hot with grated cheese and crusty Italian bread.
Serves 1 to 2 people.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the chips or noodles. Place in casserole; put the chips or noodles on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: "puppy chow"
directions: Melt your chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter.
Pour cereal in a bowl.
Pour melted mixture over cereal to coat.
Seal bowl and shake until cereal is coated with powdered sugar.
Store in airtight container.

title: summer fruit pie
directions: In a small bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, butter, sugar and cinnamon; blend well.
Press into a 9-inch quiche pan or pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Arrange fruit over crust.
Brush on Currant Glaze.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and dice eggplant and cook 10 minutes in boiling water. Drain and place in greased baking dish.
Melt butter and then blend in flour.
Add green pepper, tomatoes, onion, salt, brown sugar and bay leaf.
Cook 5 minutes or until it gets thick.
Pour over eggplant and cover with bread crumbs.
Add butter and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy microwave fudge
directions: Microwave butter in bowl on High 1 minute or until melted. Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Microwave on High 5 minutes or until begins to boil.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Mix well, scrape bowl.
Microwave 5 1/2 minutes, stir after 3 minutes.
Gradually stir in chocolate until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: fundough(nonedible, soft and pliable)
directions: Mix all together in pan.
Cook over low heat until thickened. Cool.
Knead and play.
Store in airtight plastic bag or container.
If kids' hands are washed before playing with fundough, it will keep for 6 to 9 months in refrigerator.
Soft and pliable at all times.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and 1 teaspoon soda in large mixing bowl.
Bring to a boil oleo, water and cocoa, then add sour cream and eggs.
Pour over the flour mixture.
Mix well.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix all the ingredients in an airtight container. When ready to serve, mix 1/3 cup mix with 1 cup boiling water.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix apples and candy until well blended.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve. Garnish with apple slices and additional chopped candy bars, if desired.
Makes 20 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Grill chicken on foil on top of grill.
Keep basting with sauce while cooking chicken for about 1 hour.
Chicken will get golden brown.
This recipe may also be done in oven on a pan or cookie sheet with edge to catch drippings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together until light and fluffy.
Stir in buttermilk.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop from tablespoon 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven (400°) about 8 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: minnesota cucumber pickles
directions: Slice thin the cucumbers, peppers and onions.
Mix together and place in a tightly covered dish.
Refrigerate 24 hours before using.
Add cucumbers, peppers and onions to liquid mixture as it's used up.
Great for summer picnics.

title: cupcakes
directions: Cook with a pan.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Combine lemon jello and hot water, stirring until dissolved. Pour enough 7-Up on cream cheese to dissolve.
Pour rest of 7-Up into jello.
Chill jello until thick.
Combine thickened jello and cream cheese mixture in blender and blend until fluffy.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.
Unmold on serving plate.

title: green bean dish
directions: Add water for more liquid.
Place all ingredients in kettle. Simmer on low burner until all is cooked.
Better each time this is warmed.
May be cooked in crock-pot.

title: mexitaly beef
directions: Add 2
tablespoons olive oil to a large deep frypan and cook ground
beef.
Add	chopped
onions,
garlic,
peppers, carrots, celery
and zucchini.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add
spices and
stewed
tomatoes.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Add pinto beans and
cook another 10 minutes.
This dish tastes great on macaroni or rice.

title: creamy nacho dip(for the crock pot)
directions: Fry hamburger and sausage and drain well. Mix all ingredients together in crock pot and simmer until melted and hot. Serve with nacho chips.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and stir occasionally until cold (refrigerate).
Fold in Cool Whip and drained oranges.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: texas yummy
directions: Melt the margarine and mix with flour and pecans.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Soften cream cheese.
Fold in powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Spread on top of cooked crust.
Mix together pudding and milk and put in refrigerator until set.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Spread one bowl of Cool Whip on top of pudding mixture. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Put in refrigerator until set and ready to serve.

title: old fashioned peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in baking dish.
Combine sugar, flour and milk. Cover peaches with batter.
Combine cornstarch, boiling water or peach juice, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup margarine.
Pour over batter.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Blend ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread batter in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until it springs back when lightly touched.
Cool, right side up, for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: baked fudge
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together and then add the rest, mix well.
Bake in 11x8 inch pan placed into a 13x9 inch pan of shallow water.
Bake at 300° for 45-60 minutes.
Check for crispy top but soft inside.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook and drain hamburg.
Stir in soups and seasoning.
Pour in 1 soup can of water.
Let simmer.
Cook noodles.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer noodles and hamburger.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: grandma waters' chili sauce
directions: Grind onions, peppers and tomatoes.
Add to rest of ingredients; cook until thickened, stirring occasionally (3 to 4 hours).
Pour into sterilized hot jars.
Wipe tops of jars with damp cloth and wax over.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix and bake in three layers.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Gently rinse mushrooms and pat dry.
Remove stems.
Brush caps with salad oil and place in a buttered baking dish.
Combine crab meat, eggs, mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice and 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture.
Combine remaining bread crumbs with oleo and sprinkle over mushrooms.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add egg and beat well. Add flour, baking powder and salt which have been sifted together. Blend in carrots.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
While hot ice with 2 cups powdered sugar mixed with rind of 1 orange and enough orange juice to moisten.

title: chunky-cherry-choc ice cream
directions: Combine in bowl.
Follow your ice cream freezer instructions.

title: peach punch
directions: Mix drinks together in punch bowl.
Add broken-up sherbet a little at a time.

title: jello
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water and refrigerate. When partially set, slice in banana.
If you have company, serve topped with Cool Whip in fancy bowls.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Pour jello package onto Cool Whip.
Add yogurt and some fresh fruit slices of your choice (bananas, strawberries, raspberries, blueberries, etc.).
Blend together.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Garnish with remainder fruit slices.
Refrigerate.

title: noodles with bacon and tomato
directions: Cook bacon in a large frying pan until almost done.
Drain off most of fat.
Add the onion and garlic; continue cooking with bacon until bacon is done and onion is transparent.
Add the noodles, tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper to taste and stir until mixed.
Cover pan and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking on bottom.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Combine fat, beef and onion in a skillet.
Cook until beef is lightly brown.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in ketchup and tomato sauce, heating thoroughly.
Turn into an 8-inch square pan. Cut cheese into thin strips.
Spread over beef mixture. Top with rolls.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until rolls are golden brown.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil the above ingredients until potatoes are tender.
Make a roux with 2 tablespoons butter and 1 tablespoon flour; add some liquid from soup.
Combine the mixtures and cook about 5 minutes. Add vinegar to taste, a little less than 1/4 cup.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Cook green pepper in butter for 5 minutes.
Blend in flour. Add next 3 ingredients.
Add tomato sauce, cheese and egg.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Add milk and crab meat.
Serve as a dip, on toast, or in patty shells.

title: peach iced tea
directions: Stir all ingredients together. Chill until ready to serve.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables, then mix together with cheese, sour cream and soup.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble crackers and mix with almonds and melted butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: meringue shells(about 8 shells)
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Separate 3 egg whites while the eggs are still cold (it's easier then).
When the egg whites reach room temperature, beat them at low speed until they are frothy.
Add cream of tartar and vanilla as you beat.
Very gradually add sugar and keep beating until stiff peaks form and mixture is glossy, but not dry.

title: old fashion salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, flour, mustard and salt together and stir in vinegar water mix.
Cook and stir until it boils and thickens. Slowly stir hot mixture by tablespoonfuls into beaten eggs. Return to pan and cook until creamy.
Cool.
When serving, dilute with sour cream or imitation sour cream.
This is good on leaf lettuce and sliced hard-boiled egg.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together.
Great on chips or veggies.

title: red waldorf cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat. Make a paste of coloring and cocoa and add to mixture.
Add salt, milk, flour and vanilla alternately.
Put vinegar and salt together and add to mixture last.
Bake in two 9-inch pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool, then split layers using thread in a sawing motion.
While cake is baking, start making the frosting.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Put into oblong 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. While baking, toast 4 slices bread and make bread crumbs.
After finished baking, sprinkle bread crumbs on top and pour some melted butter on top.
Bake for additional 10 minutes.

title: company potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice crosswise into 1-inch thick slices. Boil until barely tender in a small amount of water.
When cooked, remove potatoes to a baking dish.
Measure 1 cup of liquid from the potatoes and return to the pot.
Add 2 cans soup and 1/2 the cheese.
Stir while heating slowly until cheese begins to melt. Pour over potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Heat in 325° oven until sauce bubbles and cheese is melted.

title: zippy beet salad
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water in saucepan.
Heat, stirring over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Add enough water to beet juice to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Add salt and onion; chill until partially set.
Stir in beets and celery; put in mold and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: magic peach cobbler
directions: Melt stick of oleo in baking pan.
Mix milk, flour, sugar and baking powder together in bowl.
Pour this over the melted oleo. Do not stir.
Pour can of peaches and its juice over this mixture. Do not stir.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over mixture and bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: yogurt breakfast pops
directions: Combine ingredients in mixing bowl.
Spoon mixture into plastic cups, insert popsicle in the center; freeze until solid. Remove from cups, running under hot water if necessary.
Wrap in foil and replace in freezer until needed.
Makes 6 pops.

title: diet soup
directions: Cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Add package of onion soup mix.
Simmer until vegetables are done. Serve with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: spicy applesauce cake(no milk, no eggs.)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add spices and mix thoroughly, then thoroughly mix in flour.
Mix small amount of flour to nuts and raisin, then mix into butter and sugar mixture thoroughly.
Mix together 1 cup applesauce and 1 teaspoon baking soda, then mix in with other ingredients.
Grease and flour 1 tube pan or 1 standard loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini hors d'oeuvres
directions: Combine all ingredients, except zucchini.
Mix well.
Stir in squash. Spread evenly in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: white castle hamburger
directions: Mix ground beef with beef broth and beef baby food.
Fry ground beef and make 4 holes on top of the hamburger.
Add 1/4 cup dry minced onion with 1/4 cup water and pour onion on top of hamburger. Turn hamburger over so onions are frying under it.
Cook until done.

title: almond rice dish
directions: Melt margarine; add onion soup, consomme and rice. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: 1-roll-fruit
directions: Mix and bake at 350°.
Let cool, then turn onto dish towel sprinkled with sugar.
Spread filling on.
Roll tightly with wax paper, then put foil over that.
Put in freezer; remove just before serving and slice.

title: amos flewelling's famous baked beans
directions: Soak dry beans overnight.
Drain in morning and set aside. Add boiling water to dry mustard, pepper, salt, molasses, brown sugar, ginger and onion.
Bring to boil and add beans with salt pork.
Cook in crock-pot for 4 hours.

title: charcoal broiled buffalo steaks
directions: If you use the frozen buffalo steaks, thaw thoroughly before using.
Place the steaks in a long handled broiling rack and broil about 3 inches from glowing coals for 2 minutes on a side. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to season.
The main thing to remember when cooking buffalo meat is slow and low.

title: sugar white cookies
directions: Cream together the first 6 ingredients.
Add almost 4 cups of flour, then add whites of eggs beaten stiff.
Roll out and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cheese spread fudge
directions: Heat cheese and margarine in 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally until melted.
Gradually add combined sifted sugar and cocoa, stirring until smooth.
Add pecans and vanilla. Mix well.
Spread into greased 11 x 9-inch pan.
Cover and chill. Cut into squares.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Mix chicken, soup, sour cream and lemon juice.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with crushed crackers; sprinkle with poppy seed and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Oven is to be 300°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle pecans and coconut on bottom of pan.
Mix cake and pour on top of nuts and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and margarine together.
Drop by large spoonfuls on top of cake mixture.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: scallops italienne
directions: Saute shallots and garlic in hot butter until soft.
Add mushrooms, parsley and basil.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add wine and cook briskly until reduced by half.
Add tomatoes and mix well. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add scallops and stir.
Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Broil 3 inches from heat until brown and bubbly.
Serve immediately.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and oil together.
In separate bowl, mix dry ingredients and add to apple mixture.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: party nuts
directions: Mix nuts in butter.
Heat oven to 300°.
In medium bowl, until well coated, add cheese, oregano and celery salt to nuts.
Spread in ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally for 15 minutes. Stir in cereal.

title: spinach with ground beef
directions: Wash spinach very good; cut medium.
Heat butter; add ground beef and fry until brown.
Add garlic and cilantro.
Fry together for five minutes, then add salt, pepper and allspice, then add water.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat.
Cook for 5 minutes, then add spinach.
Stir good.
Cook for 1/2 hour; turn heat off, then add lemon juice.
Garnish with fried pine nuts.
Eat with cooked rice.
Serves 6 people.

title: potato rolls(chilled)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, Crisco, salt, mashed potato and eggs.
Gradually add flour.
Chill dough 1 to 2 hours or overnight.

title: cajun cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meatballs
directions: Soak the bread in milk.
Mix the ground beef, onion, salt, pepper and bread together to form a ball.
Fry until done.
Put in crock-pot with barbecue sauce.
Serve warm.

title: low calorie vegetable soup
directions: To a large saucepan, add juice, water and bouillon cubes. Make it come to a boil and add chopped onion.
Cook for about 5 minutes.
Add all the vegetables and the parsley.
Cook until vegetables are at desired consistency.
Serve with rice, pasta or with crackers.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Cream cheese and margarine together.
Add flour, salt and paprika.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: butter ball cookies
directions: Mix butter and vanilla.
Stir flour and salt in mixture.
Add nuts; mix.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Roll in confectioners sugar twice.

title: chicken alfredo
directions: Coat chicken with flour, then dip in beaten eggs and roll in bread crumbs flavored with
2 tablespoons grated cheese.
In a little oil, fry on both sides to brown.
Put in baking dish and season with salt, pepper and parsley.
Melt butter; add heavy cream and 1/2 cup Italian cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Put 1 slice of Mozzarella cheese on each piece of chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.
Can be made in advance.

title: mushroom cheese puffs
directions: Soften oleo and cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Spread on 1/2 English muffin.
Cut each into quarters. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen before baking.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease glass pie dish.
Combine apples, 1/2 cup of sugar and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Arrange in single layer in prepared dish.
Combine eggs, flour, baking powder and remaining sugar in medium bowl.
Stir in oil until smooth.
Pour batter over apples.
Bake until golden, about 40 to 45 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve warm.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Needs to be made several hours before serving or overnight for best flavor.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pineapple with pudding. Mix until thickened. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well; cool and serve.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water.
Make cheese sauce; saute onion in margarine.
Mix broth, milk and garlic and thicken with flour.
Add Velveeta and broccoli and serve.

title: smoked sausage and potatoes
directions: Wash and quarter potatoes, slice smoked sausage in large casserole dish.
Melt butter, stir in onion soup.
Pour over potatoes and sausages.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°, covered, then uncover and cook 15 minutes.

title: seafood courtbouillon(q-be-on)
directions: *You may use chunks or filets of flounder, drum, redfish, scamp, sheephead, shrimp or oysters.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese to soften.
Add condensed milk.
Beat again until smooth.
Add vanilla pudding and water; beat until smooth. Fold in cool whip.
Put 1/2 into pie crust, add pie filling or fruit, add remaining filling.
Refrigerate.

title: bran nut bread(muffins)
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda, powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, stir together bran and milk.
Let stand for 2 minutes or until cereal is softened.
Add eggs and oil.
Beat well.
Stir in nuts, vanilla, cinnamon and raisins. Add flour mix, stirring just until moistened.
Spread in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before removing.
Cool completely on wire rack before slicing.
Muffins cook 20 minutes at 325°.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat egg slightly; add milk and salad oil.
Stir lightly.
Pour into greased 10-inch square pan or spoon into cast-iron corn bread stick pan.
(Heat pan in oven first.)
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit punch with lemon ice
directions: Mix juices, tea, sugar and water and chill 12 hours.
Add ginger ale just before serving over lemon ice.
Sprinkle with lemon rind.

title: cheese balls
directions: Grate cheddar and Swiss coarsley.
Crumble blue cheese finely using a fork, mix all together with softened cream cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Shape into balls about 1 inch in diameter. Roll in nuts.
Put on platter or cookie sheet lined with wax paper chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour before serving.

title: cinnamon crunch bars
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cover bottom of a greased 10 x 15-inch pan with graham crackers.
Spread nuts evenly over crackers.

title: butter balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix butter and sifted powdered sugar thoroughly.
Then stir the vanilla into the mixture.
Add the flour and salt.
After these ingredients are well mixed, add the walnuts and then make 1/2-inch balls.
Bake them on an ungreased cookie sheet,
approximately 2 1/4 inches apart at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Cool well and roll in the unsifted powdered sugar.

title: date and prune squares
directions: Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Gradually beat sugar into eggs.
Add butter, water and rind.
Stir in dates and nuts. Gradually add flour mixture, beating well.
Spread batter evenly in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool; cut into bars.
Sprinkle with or roll in confectioners sugar, if desired.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook the apples.
(Measure the water you put in to cook the apples; take that away from the 2 gallons.)
Put apples through sieve.
I put 2 gallons water in big cooker and measure how far this is down from top of cooker.
Then, add applesauce and cook down to the amount water was.
Add sugar and spices.
Be sure to mix sugar and spices very good (dry) before adding to apples, or until thick enough to form a skin on top when a little is put on saucer and cooled off.
Makes a difference in the kind of apples you have.
Some are thicker than others (you have to do a little guessing about the water).
Don't put in 2 gallons when you start with applesauce.
It usually takes about a day to bake a big batch. Hope you have good luck.

title: angel food cake surprise
directions: Prepare angel food cake.
Prepare pudding or jello.
Allow time for jello to set.
Slice off top 1/3 of cake and set aside. Cut a "moat" out of remainder of cake.
Fill "moat" with pudding and bananas or jello and fruit.
Return top to cake and frost with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Garnish with extra fruit and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all together and pour into a casserole dish.
Cook at 350° until brown.
Makes 4 servings.
